title: noodles
directions: Mix milk, salt and eggs.
Add to flour.
Place plenty of flour on counter and roll out.
Leave out 20 minutes, rolled out.
Fold with plenty of flour between folds, then cut.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften	cream
cheese.	Add onion, Worcestershire sauce and shrimp.
Mix
together,
mashing shrimp until smooth. Form into mound. Top	with
cocktail sauce, if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: fusilli with parsley-mushroom sauce
directions: In a small bowl combine the yogurt, cheese, parsley, sour cream and pepper; cover and refrigerate.
In a large kettle cook the fusilli according to package directions, omitting the salt. Meanwhile, heat the olive oil in a heavy 7-inch skillet over moderately high heat for 1 minute.
Add the mushrooms, onion and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally for 5 to 7 minutes or until the onion is soft.
Add the wine to the mushroom mixture and cook for 1 to 2 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Add the yogurt-cheese mixture and heat through; do not boil or the sauce will curdle.

title: fresh coconut cake(well worth the time involved)
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Alternately add milk and flour, creaming after each addition.
Add vanilla and beat with mixer until very creamy.
Grease 3 cake pans with Crisco and dust with self-rising flour.
Divide cake batter evenly among the prepared pans.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 325° to 350°. Cool completely before icing.
If desired, sprinkle 1 teaspoon of coconut milk over each layer before icing.

title: mary's layered tostada dip
directions: In an 8-inch pie plate, layer bean dip, then combine avocados and 4 tablespoons mayonnaise and 2 tablespoons sour cream.
Layer that on top of bean dip.
Then combine remaining sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add the taco seasoning to top.
Sprinkle cheese and vegetables on top.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Beat together in a medium bowl the milk, mayonnaise, sugar and self-rising flour.
If necessary, add a little more (no more than 1/2 cup) of the self-rising flour so that dough can be dropped from spoon and hold its shape.
Mix in grated cheese.
Drop by spoonfuls 1 inch apart on greased baking sheet in about 9 equal mounds.
Brush tops a bit with butter and sprinkle with more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Dust with garlic salt to taste as soon as they come out of the oven.
Makes 9 biscuits.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Mix the above ingredients together and pour into a 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375 degrees for 40 - 50 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: corn dodgers
directions: Place cornmeal in large bowl; make well in center.
Add salt and boiling water.
Stirring until mixed thoroughly.
Shape hot mixture into 3-inch patties with help of a spoon.
Fry in butter until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with bean soup or with butter and maple syrup with bacon and eggs.
Yield:
12 patties. Recipe over 100 years.

title: florida champagne
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and water; boil 3 minutes.
Chill. In large punch bowl, combine chilled juices and sugar water mixture.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale to juices.
Place flavored ice ring or ice cubes in punch bowl.

title: spinach madeleine
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain, reserving liquor.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, stirring only until smooth.
Add onions. Cook until soft.
Add liquor slowly, stirring to avoid lumps.
Add milk.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Add seasonings and cheese (cut into smallish pieces).
Stir until melted.
Combine with spinach.
Serve immediately or refrigerate overnight.
May be topped with breadcrumbs.
May be frozen.
It is really better the second day!

title: kool-aid frozen cups
directions: Fill a 2-quart pitcher half full with water.
Empty package of your favorite flavor of Kool-Aid into pitcher.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Finish filling with water.
Chill or take 12 (7 ounce) plastic cups and place in freezer.
Freeze until frozen.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
While still hot, poke holes all over cake with long tined fork.

title: winter squash and apple compote
directions: Bring the juice or cider to a boil in a medium-size saucepan. Add the winter squash and continue cooking for 10 to 15 minutes. Add the apples.
When the pot continues to boil again, sprinkle the sugar and (if desired) the cinnamon red hearts on the apples. Continue to cook until apples and squash are tender.
It is possible you might need some additional apple juice (add as needed).
You should be able to see the juice near the top of the apples when done.
When taking out of the saucepan, into a bowl, mix the apples and squash.
This is a good side dish with meat or chicken.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Marinate chicken in salad dressing 30 minutes to overnight. With chicken breast flat, top with 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese. Roll and use toothpick to secure.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with cheese and bake until cheese is slightly melted.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in parsley and seasonings. In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture. Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan or 11-inch quiche pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture evenly into crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and salt, blending well.
Pour in milk and vanilla.
Stir well.
Sprinkle unbaked pie shell with nutmeg and pour mixture in.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna patties
directions: Pour tuna in mixing bowl. Add the eggs and mix well. Crush the crackers real good and add to mixture. Add flour and mix well. Make into patties.
Fry them in oil until golden brown.

title: watergate cake
directions: Put in mixer bowl all at one time and beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Add shortening to flour and blend.
Add milk and mix until dough will form into a ball.
Turn dough out on a floured board; knead lightly until you can work the dough out to a smooth surface.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix well until sugar is dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and stir.
Pour into 2 clean 1/2 gallon cardboard milk containers. Close with paper clips and freeze solid.
One hour before serving, remove frozen slush from freezer and place in punch bowl.
Let sit until serving time.
With fork, chop and scrape until well broken up.
Add ginger ale.
Mix and serve.

title: stuffed pasta
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain pasta shells as directed on package.
Spread spaghetti sauce in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients, except pesto.
Fill each pasta shell with about 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture.
Arrange filled shells on spaghetti sauce.
Cover and bake approximately 45 minutes or until hot.
Serve with pesto.

title: old time lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Stir in water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick (3 to 5 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir a small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks; then pour into remaining hot mixture in pan.
Bring to a boil and cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add lemon peel and butter.
Slowly stir in lemon juice.
Cool to lukewarm; pour into pastry shell.

title: kraut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Make a thick paste with flour and milk.
Coat each ball and then deep fry until brown.
Can freeze and then heat in oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut oatmeal macaroons
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder, salt and soda. Sift again.
Cream the butter; add sugars gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour, oatmeal and coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into small balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350° to 375°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: pink peppermint pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Heat marshmallows and milk in a saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, just until marshmallows are melted. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla, salt, peppermint extract and food coloring.
Refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until the mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.
Beat whipping cream in a chilled bowl until stiff.
Stir marshmallow mixture until blended; fold into whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: vegetable juice cocktail
directions: Place measured tomatoes and all ingredients except lemon juice in a 12 quart or larger pot and simmer for about 30 minutes or until all the vegetables are soft.
Remove bay leaves.
Press vegetables through a fine sieve or put through a food mill to remove seeds, skins and pulp.
Return juice to pot, stir in lemon juice to taste and bring to boil.
Quickly pour into clean hot quart jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace; seal.
Process in boiling water about 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 7 quarts.

title: indian pilaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and rice; cook and stir until rice is yellow and onion is tender. Stir in next 5 seasonings.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Heat chicken broth to boiling; stir into rice mixture.
Cover tightly.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: marinade
directions: Marinate meat and vegetables several hours or overnight.
(Do marinate meat, carrots, celery and onions.
Do not marinate peppers and mushrooms.)

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Slice carrots and boil in salt water until fork-tender. Drain.
When cool, alternate layers of carrots, pepper rings and onion slices (slice thin).
Make a marinade of remaining ingredients.
Blender is ideal.
Pour mixture over vegetables and refrigerate either in jar or covered dish.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ham and swiss quiche
directions: Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Add ham, cheese and onion.
Stir to mix.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir well.
Add next four ingredients.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes until bubbly.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Heat in large kettle, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Makes one gallon or 16 servings.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Line bottom and sides of spring-form pan with ladyfingers. Set aside.
Whip cream until stiff.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold whipped cream into cream cheese mixture. Spoon layer of whipped cream mixture and then layer of pineapple pie filling on ladyfingers.
Repeat with 2 layers of ladyfingers, cream mixture and pie filling.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: microwave swiss steak
directions: Put steak in microwave casserole dish.
Add tomato sauce and green chilies.
Mix.
Add water.
Mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes in large oven (15 in small oven) on High.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Saute chicken cubes; add broth and bring to a boil.
Add salsa, rice, beans, lime juice and cilantro.
Return to a slow boil, then turn down heat and cook on low for 10 minutes.
Serve in a bowl with shredded cheese on top.
This soup is best when made a day before serving.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Grate zucchini and add to mixture.
In second bowl sift together flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add raisins and nuts to flour mixture.
Stir flour mixture into zucchini mixture.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut the tops and bottoms off of the tomatoes and slice in half crosswise.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and dip lightly in flour.
Fry in hot butter until brown on both sides.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Cook bacon and then chop it.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Boil ingredients; add pickling spices or simmer until sugar melts.
Pack cucumbers in jars. Pour liquid over cucumbers and seal jar. Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 2 quarts or 4 pints.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Combine other ingredients (except crumbs) to the broccoli.
Pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
May be refrigerated or frozen before cooking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix 1 can celery soup and 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Bring to a boil and set aside.

title: * mock chicken turnovers *
directions: Melt fat; add flour.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot milk. Add and cook until thick.
Add flaked tuna and egg.
Make pie pastry and roll out into 4-inch squares.
Place a spoonful and seal.
Cut a gash in top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 or 14 squares.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: my mom's baked beans
directions: Prepare dried beans according to package directions or 8 cups boiling, salted water (1 teaspoon salt).
Add beans and take off heat to let soak 1 hour or longer.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Place in refrigerator for a short time.
Take part of the dough and roll out.
Cut in desired shapes.
Place on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam, then take out more dough and roll out and cut, adding leftover dough to part fresh each time.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 minutes.
The best sugar cookies!

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Cream until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in almond and vanilla extracts, flour and milk.

title: sweet red dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs. Pour 2 cups batter into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: veal in lemon butter sauce
directions: Dredge veal cutlets in flour; salt and pepper.
Heat butter in hot skillet.
Add meat and brown.
Reduce heat and cover pan. Cook for 20 minutes.
Turn veal 2 or 3 times.
Transfer meat to warm platter and keep warm.
To juice, add wine, lemon juice and remaining butter.
When butter has melted, pour over meat and serve.
Serve immediately.

title: ricotta puffs
directions: Mix together eggs; add Ricotta, sugar, baking powder and flour. Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
In saucepan, pour oil.
When it is hot, drop dough by the tablespoonfuls into oil.
Puffs will turn themselves when browned.
Remove from oil and place on paper towel to drain.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Eat them hot.

title: red christmas cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Mix food color and cocoa together.
Add to mixture.
Blend well.
Mix buttermilk and vanilla.
Add flour and salt, alternating with buttermilk and vanilla to mix.
Combine white vinegar and soda.
Add to the mixture while still foaming.
Bake in two cake pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Combine all the ingredients and place in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: bean casserole(excellent!)
directions: Brown ground beef; put on side.
Fry bacon and onion.
Combine all ingredients and simmer one hour or put in crock-pot for a few hours.
The longer you cook, the better.
Can be main meal or side dish.
Great for parties.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine them with the rest of the ingredients, except corn flakes.
Place in a 3-quart casserole or large flat baking dish.
Sprinkle buttered corn flakes on top of potatoes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in bottom of baking dish; salt and pepper. Place onions and potatoes over chops.
Add soups; cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add oil and zucchini, then add dry ingredients.
Stir in pineapple, nuts, raisins and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° one hour or until done.

title: beef dip
directions: Melt cheese in chafing dish.
Tear beef in small bits and add to cheese.
Keep warm.

title: golden harvest muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 18 muffin cups with paper baking cups or grease bottoms and sides.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off.
In a large bowl, combine all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves. Add apples, carrots, coconut, raisin and walnuts.
Mix well.
Add oil, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Stir just until moistened.
Fill lined muffin cups 3/4 full.

title: maple pecan pralines
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a Dutch oven. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Stir in pecans. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches soft stage (236°). Remove from heat and stir in the flavoring.
Beat with a wooden spoon 5 to 8 minutes until it begins to thicken.
Working quickly, drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix and pat into cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes; cool.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Place broccoli in a casserole dish.
Combine the soup, mayonnaise, egg and 3/4 cup cheese; pour over broccoli.
Top with remaining cheese and breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Serves 6 to 8 people.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Heat oven to 400°.
Put broccoli in casserole dish.
Beat soup and milk together until smooth.
Pour over broccoli in dish.
Sprinkle cheese over broccoli.
Mix Bisquick with butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over cheese. Bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: country-style barbecued ribs
directions: Cook ribs, covered, in enough boiling salted water to cover, for 45 - 60 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Cook onion and garlic in hot oil till tender.
Stir in tomato sauce and the next 8 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Stir once or twice. Grill ribs over slow coals about 45 minutes or until done.
Turn every 15 minutes.
Brush with sauce till coated.
Serves 6.

title: liz wood's chili cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine beaten eggs, cheese and chilies.
In a medium frying pan, saute onion and beef together until beef is no longer pink and onion is limp.
Drain off any fat and add meat and onion to the egg mixture.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan and bake 45 minutes or until set. Cool and cut into squares for serving.
(Can also be served as a main dish for 4.)

title: festive ham glaze
directions: Bake ham at 350° for 1 hour.
Melt butter.
Stir in preserves, mustard and brown sugar.
Brush ham generously with apricot glaze. Bake 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally with glaze.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican shepherd's pie(for a crowd!)
directions: Saute meat, onions and peppers.
When cooked, add taco seasoning. Mix well.
Add salsa, water and Tabasco.
Mix well. Layer meat mixture into four shallow hotel pans (or eight 9 x 13-inch pans).
Add layer of corn, then layer of potatoes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake approximately 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 80.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar in mixing bowl and beat at high speed for at least 15 minutes.
Pour crushed graham crackers into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place cream cheese, sugar and egg mixture on top of crumbs.
Slice bananas and dip in pineapple juice.
Place on top of mixture.
Top with pineapple and spread prepared Dream Whip on top. Sprinkle nuts and crushed crackers on top.
Refrigerate.

title: grilled barbecue catfish
directions: Clean fish and place on sheet of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle on salt, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Slice onion and place on fish.
Wrap aluminum foil around fish loosely.
Cook approximately 45 minutes on low heat.

title: rolls
directions: Put oil, sugar and salt in a large bowl and pour boiling water over it. Dissolve yeast in cup of warm water. Add 2 cups of flour to bowl when lukewarm to make a batter. Stir well. Add eggs and yeast. Stir again. Add rest of flour and stir until it leaves sides of bowl. Cover with cloth. Set in warm place to rise double. Punch down. Let rise again, then make into rolls. Put in pan and let rise double. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cabbage and apple slaw
directions: Combine cabbages, apples, carrots, peppers and red onion in large bowl.
Blend mayonnaise, 1/4 of the walnuts, sour cream, dill, mustard, honey and vinegar in processor until smooth.
Toss with cabbage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, sprinkle with remaining walnuts and garnish with green onions.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package instructions; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Cover for 45 minutes
and uncover for 10 to 15 minutes.)

title: spice dip
directions: Mix sugar with spices.
Fold in whipped topping.
Do not overmix.
Serve with assorted fruits, cookies or cake cubes. Makes 1 2/3 cups with approximately 6 calories per teaspoon.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Tear biscuits into quarters and roll into balls.
Put in bowl; melt margarine and add sugar, cinnamon, raisins and nuts.
Stir well.
Pour over balls and mix well. Place in a Bundt pan that has been greased.
Bake approximately 30 minutes.

title: sweetened southern tea
directions: Heat 2 quarts water to boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in the sugar until dissolved.
Add tea bags.
Cover and allow to steep for about 5 minutes. Remove tea bags. Add remaining water. Serve over ice.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: egg-cheese ball
directions: Mix all together with enough mayonnaise to hold together. Line a bowl with plastic wrap before pouring mixture in.
Mold in refrigerator.
Turn out on a plate.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crackers.

title: new horizons chicken
directions: Coat chicken thoroughly with flour.
Brown slowly in hot oil with garlic.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add mushroom liquid, soy sauce, catsup, wine and onion to chicken, stirring to combine.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Stir in mushrooms and olives; bring to boil.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and pour over salad; mix. Let stand 1 hour or more.

title: apple and oat bran muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together flour, oat bran, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Set aside. In a small bowl, combine buttermilk, egg whites and oil.
Add to dry ingredients. Stir just until moistened. Stir in shredded apples.
Store batter, tightly covered, in the refrigerator for up to 5 days.

title: church potato salad
directions: This is the recipe we use for chicken suppers.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Peel and slice one eggplant.
Steam until tender and drain. Mash and beat until smooth.
Add egg, flour, salt and baking powder.
Form into patties and fry in deep, hot fat.

title: grape butter
directions: Boil for
minutes,
then
put through food press to remove seeds and skins.
Put in jars and seal.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter for 3 minutes; add stock, celery, carrots,
salt,
pepper, bay leaf and thyme.
Simmer gently 10 to 15 minutes.
Add fish;
simmer 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf. Make smooth
thin
paste
of 1 cup milk and flour.
Add to hot mixture and
cook,	stirring, until thick.	Stir in remaining milk, cream, crab meat and clams.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put boned chicken in bottom of long casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together and spread over chicken.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour melted butter evenly over top of crackers.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add salt and cream of tartar and continue beating until egg whites are stiff.
Add sugar a tablespoon at a time, beating constantly until glossy.
Mix in vanilla and fold in chips.
Drop on greased cookie sheets with teaspoon.
Place in oven.
Turn off oven and let cookies stand overnight.
Do not open oven for at least 5 hours. Yields 4 dozen.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix oil, parsley flakes, powder, dill weed and dressing mix together.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Mix well and store in an airtight container.
Better than popcorn!

title: chicken crisp
directions: Mix dry Italian dressing with flour in large mixing bowl. Place melted butter in a smaller bowl.
Coat chicken and pieces in butter first, then flour mixture.
Place in large baking pan and bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.

title: spiced cocoa
directions: Combine water, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in cocoa, sugar and milk.
Heat, do not boil.
Add vanilla.
Makes 4 cups.

title: grandmama's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternately with flour.
Add lemon and vanilla and mix well.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar and salt; cook 10 minutes.
Let cool. Mix gelatine and hot water together.
Let cool until syrupy, then combine with pineapple mixture.
Mix whipped topping as directed on package.
Cream the cheese and mix whipped topping.
Mix everything together and chill.

title: butter cookies(roll type)
directions: Cream butter; add powdered sugar until fluffy. Add beaten egg and vanilla. Add dry ingredients. Blend into creamed mixture.

title: special potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets the night before until done.
Let cool.
Chop or shred and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, melt other ingredients. Pour over potatoes.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: no-cook banana pudding
directions: Mix 1/2 Cool Whip with pudding, sour cream, milk and vanilla flavoring.
Put layer of vanilla wafers, layer of sliced bananas and layer of pudding mixture in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle crushed vanilla wafers on top. Refrigerate.

title: blueberry melba(serves 8 to 10)
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in Port and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened and translucent.
Stir in blueberries; simmer about 5 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
To serve, arrange peach halves cut side up in 6 sherbet glasses.
Top each with 1 scoop ice cream.
Spoon cooled blueberry sauce evenly over each.
Colors are very pretty and cool looking for a summer dessert.

title: buttermilk griddle cakes
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Make a well in the center of the dry mixture; set aside.
Separate eggs, reserving the whites.
In another bowl, lightly beat egg yolks, buttermilk and melted butter to blend. Add to dry ingredients.
(Batter will be slightly lumpy.)

title: 1 egg yellow cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kentucky corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Pour in large greased casserole (9 x 9-inch) about 3 inches deep.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a blender until frothy. Yields 5 (1/2 cup each) servings; 280 total (56 per 1/2 cup) calories.
Exchange:
1 1/2 fruit.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Mixture will be very thick.
Do not use mixer.
Bake in oblong pan for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy pot roast
directions: Put all in crock-pot for 10 hours.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: yeast bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water in a large bowl. Stir until dissolved. Blend in sugar, shortening, salt and egg; add 1/2 flour. Beat thoroughly with a wooden spoon. Add remaining half flour and beat about 2 minutes, until smooth.

title: old-fashioned baked ham
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons of juice; set aside. Place ham in a baking pan; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, cloves, mustard and vinegar in a small bowl; stir in reserved pineapple juice.
Score ham; place pineapple slices and cherries on top of ham.
Spoon glaze over fruit and ham.
Bake for another 40 to 45 minutes, basting occasionally.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate peanut squares
directions: Microwave 3/4 cup margarine with 2 squares chocolate 1 to 2 minutes or until melted when stirred.
Stir in crumbs, coconut and peanuts.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan; chill 30 minutes.

title: coconut cherry bars
directions: Spread dough in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Cool slightly, then cut into 40 bars.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Make Jell-O with only 1 cup boiling water.
Add strawberries, bananas, walnuts and pineapple.
Pour 3/4 of mixture into mold. Let jell until firm.
Spread sour cream over Jell-O mixture.
Pour remaining mixture over sour cream and jell until solid. Delicious!!

title: mary's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and spices.
Gradually stir in milk and then pumpkin.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken cheese pie
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo until tender.
Stir in flour and broth.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add chicken, carrots and egg.
Turn into pie shell and top with slices of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese turns light brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Make the day before serving.
Keeps 3 days.

title: apple bars
directions: Combine in order given. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Glaze or frost, if desired.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread out on paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Layer 1 package cookies in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine and blend cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Top cookie layer with filling.
Layer 2nd package of cookies on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pizza noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles to desired doneness as directed on package; drain.
Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook ground beef, onions and green pepper for 7 to 9 minutes or until meat is browned and vegetables are crisp-tender; drain.
Add noodles, Italian seasoning, pepperoni, olives, tomato sauce and tomato paste; mix well.
Fold in 1 cup of the cheese.
Pour mixture into ungreased 2 quart baking dish.
Top with remaining 1 cup cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated and cheese begins to brown.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: bacon-wrapped tuna
directions: Cut tuna into 6 steaks each, about 1 inch thick.
Remove any skin or bone.

title: spinach-broccoli cauliflower casserole
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Mix with spinach and onions.
To make light white sauce, melt low-fat oleo in pan; add flour and mix.
Add low-fat or skim milk (powdered works well) and blend, cooking until thickened and smooth.
Add little dill and mustard to taste.
Pour over veggies in casserole. Sprinkle with grated cheese or bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: packaged cake(microwave)
directions: Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) round glass cake dishes.
Prepare cake mix as to package directions.
Heat one layer at a time uncovered on roast for 8 to 9 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: pistachio nut salad-dessert
directions: Mix together pudding mix and milk and heat 2 minutes.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Save some Cool Whip to frost top.
Fold in remaining Cool Whip.
Pour into an 8 x 11-inch loaf pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Frost with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
At holiday time, can also top with red maraschino cherries.

title: it's better than potato salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer to bowl. Cover; chill.
Add mayonnaise or salad dressing, celery, onion, mustard and salt to chilled rice.
Mix well; cover and chill. Stir in remaining ingredients before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple with juice to a boil. Add gelatin and mix well. Cool. Add buttermilk, nondairy whipped topping and nuts.
Mix well. Refrigerate.
Let congeal.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Mix all of mixture with Cool Whip.
Divide into two pie shells.
Refrigerate for 6 or more hours.

title: graham gems
directions: Mix ingredients well and put in greased or paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: white chocolate bark
directions: Stir glace cherries and pecans into melted chocolate.
Spread mixture into a thin layer on a greased cookie sheet.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares.
Store covered at room temperature. Yields about 2 pounds of candy.
This is great for Christmas.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together in large bowl with mixer. Mix until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spoon into graham cracker crumb crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.

title: marinated fruit salad
directions: Cut top off cantaloupe.
Remove seeds, etc.
Fill with fruit and rum.
Replace top and refrigerate overnight.
Especially good to take on picnics.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Pour into buttered baking dish and bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, water and sugar in pan.
Bring to boil and put in bowl to cool.
Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk; mix until smooth.
Add pineapple and baby food to Jell-O mixture.
Mix this with cream cheese and milk; add nuts.
Pour into mold or sheet cake pan.
Chill until firm.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan the first 6 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread on top as frosting.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: jalapeno pepper bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour batter into a well-greased 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: barbecue for 10 halves of chicken
directions: Beat egg, oil and vinegar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Just heat, do not boil.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: In greased casserole dish, place chicken pieces.
Spread can of whole cranberry sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle dried onion soup mix over top, then pour over all the Catalina dressing.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and cover for only 1/2 the baking time.
Serve with rice.

title: valentine sugar cookies
directions: Cream 1 cup margarine and 2 cups sugar into bowl; add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Stir in cream.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well; stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Roll out very thin on floured surface; cut with cookie cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet; bake in preheated 400° oven until brown.
Cool.
Combine remaining sugar, milk and remaining margarine in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook until mixture forms soft ball when dropped in water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and food coloring glaze.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cream the potatoes. Brown hamburger meat. Take 3 tablespoons flour and milk; mix well. After meat is done, drain.
Pour gravy over hamburger meat.
Put into baking dish a layer of creamed potatoes and a layer of meat.
Last layer should be creamed potatoes.
Garnish top of creamed potatoes with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese, if desired.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil cut chicken and debone.
Cut up (reserve broth).
Melt butter.
Add soup, sour cream, broth, carrot and dry stuffing. Mix well.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, cooking oil and water; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each egg.
Add strawberries and beat well.
Bake in layer cake pans 25 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake in greased pans approximately 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves (about 3 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 2 1/2 size pans). Cool 5 minutes in pan and then remove to cooling rack and cool completely.

title: dukes skillet(quick hot dish)
directions: Brown the meat in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Mix together oleo, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until fluffy, then add honey, flour, wheat germ, baking powder, soda and other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix all together. Pour into a buttered 1-quart casserole. Top with crushed Ritz or Town House crackers. Drizzle with 1/4-cup melted butter. Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexican skillet fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cinnamon, salt and milk in an electric skillet.
Set thermostat at 280°.
Bring to boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off skillet.
Add marshmallows, chocolate chips, pecans and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows and chocolate chips are melted and smoothly blended.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch square buttered dish.
Cool before cutting into squares. Yields 2 pounds.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes two pies.

title: salsa
directions: *Italian tomatoes (Roma) are best in salsa.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Heat oil in 3-quart saucepan.
When hot, add onions and saute until translucent.
Add green peppers and saute until slightly softened.
Add rest of ingredients and mix together well.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix topping, cake mix and egg well.
Shape into small round balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together with dressing.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix together 2 tablespoons warm water and 1 package dry yeast. Sift dry ingredients and cut in the shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
This makes a sticky dough.
Add flour (extra if necessary) and roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut as biscuits and roll in melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix and spread into 9-inch pie pan.
Jab with fork a few times and bake 6 to 8 minutes at 450°.
Cool.
Fill with sliced strawberries.

title: dump peach cobbler
directions: Dump together flour, sugar, milk and baking powder; mix.
Spray baking dish with nonstick spray.
Pour mixture into baking dish. On top of this dump sliced peaches with syrup.
Chop oleo on top and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for some 20 to 30 minutes.

title: forget um's
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix 1 cup sugar and beat until sugar dissolves.
Add and mix by hand the chocolate chips and nuts.

title: key lime toasted pecan muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

Combine flour and sugar. Stir to mix. Combine eggs, yogurt, whipping cream, and coconut flavoring. Mix well. Stir in toasted pecans. Spoon into well greased muffin tin, filling each cup 2/3 full. Bake for 13 to 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of one of the muffins. Makes 10 large muffins.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well; place in covered container and chill, preferably overnight.
Roll out very thin, cut into circles and put on a cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by spoon into hot oil and cook until done. Drain on brown paper.

title: spring breeze cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually add and beat sugar in. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Blend well.
Pour into crust.
Chill at last 4 hours (or until set). Garnish with strawberries if desired.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger, onions, green peppers and garlic.
Bring to boil 4 cups water and 1/2 pound spaghetti, broken into smaller pieces.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes.
Add hamburger.
Stir in tomatoes and ketchup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese. Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix alternately with flour, fruits and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: In a bowl slowly mix the first 5 ingredients with a mixer. Add salad oil slowly while blending, add celery seed and paprika.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Sprinkle cranberries with 2 tablespoons sugar; set aside.
Sift remaining sugar, flour, baking powder and salt into large mixing bowl.
In separate bowl, beat egg, milk and oil.
Make a hole in center of dry ingredients; pour in liquid ingredients.
Stir only until mixed; do not overmix.
Add berries and lemon peel.
Fill greased standard or extra-large muffin cups with mixture.
Sprinkle tops of muffins with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 400° about 18 minutes for standard size muffins or about 22 minutes for extra large muffins.
Yields 12 standard size or 6 extra large muffins.

title: chocolate sour cream drops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a saucepan over low heat, melt 1 cup of the chocolate chips. In a large bowl, beat sugars and margarine until fluffy. Add sour cream, vanilla, eggs and melted chocolate. Mix well. Add flour, baking powder and baking soda, a little at a time. Mix well. Stir in remaining
1 cup chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon onto parchment-lined cookie sheets 2-inches apart. Bake for 7 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in order and chill several hours.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: southern icebox pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar slowly and beat, then add vanilla.
Fold in cracker crumbs and nuts.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Bake until golden brown (about 30 minutes).
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut (also nuts if desired).

title: chris' corn salad
directions: Drain corn well, also pimentos.
Add onions (including tops). Toss all vegetables together lightly.
Add mayonnaise. Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well.

title: carol's rosettes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add to oil, flavoring, sugar and baking powder. Add slowly to 4 1/2 cups flour. Knead, roll out and shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked potatoes and onions
directions: Peel potatoes and make cross wise slices on them about 1/4 inch apart; do not cut all the way through.
About every second slice, insert a slice of onion, sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place 1 tbsp. butter on top of each potato.
Wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Tear into pieces and place in baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers and pour on top.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: spice tea
directions: To make 1 cup tea, mix 3 tablespoons mix to a cup of boiling water.

title: homemade chicken soup
directions: Put chicken in large 6-quart boiler with celery, onions and salt and pepper; cook until chicken is done.
Debone and cut up chicken; return to pot.
Add carrots, green beans, tomatoes, corn and all seasonings.
Add potatoes, okra, cabbage and turnips about 30 minutes before soup is done.
Makes about 6 quarts and can be stored in deep freeze.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Add powdered sugar. Mix well.
Make into balls.
Place on wax paper on cookie sheet for 2 days in refrigerator.

title: ziti with broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook ziti in boiling water until al dente (still a little firm). Drain pasta and place in a large bowl; set aside.
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat and saute garlic until lightly brown, about 1 minute.
Combine garlic, broccoli, Parmesan cheese and heavy cream with ziti.
Spoon mixture into large baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: charleston vegetable dip
directions: Blend thoroughly and chill.
Excellent for vegies.
Every time I use this dip, the recipe is requested.

title: festive potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Cool.
Dice potatoes.
Pour oil over potatoes.
Add vinegar, salt, pepper, sliced olives, diced pickles, shredded carrots, pimentos (diced), finely chopped green pepper, grated onions and grated cabbage; mix well.
Add mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Serve cold.

title: brisket of beef roast
directions: Season meat well with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Add onion soup mix to both sides.
Place in a roaster or cake pan.
Add amount of water wanted for gravy.
Usually 3/4 to 1-inch deep. Cover tightly and roast in slow oven at 325° to 350° until tender. Takes 2 1/2 or 3 hours.
Turn the meat in about 1 1/2 hours. Cool in refrigerator at least 1 day.
Trim off fat, slice and set back into gravy; reheat for serving.

title: (hessen) sauerkraut and brats
directions: Fry bacon, chopped with onions, until bacon is crisp and onions are translucent.
In a Dutch oven, transfer sautee mixture; next add sauerkraut and applesauce.
Simmer over low to medium heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Brown the brats in the frying pan. (Cook thoroughly).
Cut in half and place in sauerkraut.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: simple stir-fry for turkey leftovers
directions: In large skillet saute vegetables and onion in oil for 6 to 8 minutes until crisp-tender.
Combine stir-fry sauce and turkey. Add to vegetable mixture; heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: garlic-blue cheese vinaigrette
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Add blue cheese; stir mixture before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in a meat loaf pan.
Pat it down.
Put a little ketchup on the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yum-yum icebox cake
directions: Mix instant pudding mix with milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Layer whole graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour 1/2 pudding mix over crackers; repeat ending with top layer of graham crackers.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Mix vegetables.
In a separate bowl, combine soup, oil, vinegar and remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold as a salad or hot as a vegetable.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix well and add 2 cups cold water.
Freeze.

title: giant raisin bran cookies
directions: Sift together Kellogg's Raisin Bran cereal, flours and baking soda; set aside.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix instant pudding, Jell-O and whipped cream well.
Add pineapple and sour cream mixing well with other ingredients.
Add marshmallows; stir in well.
Chill for 2 hours, then serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Separate and spread in two pizza pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: family gathering spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir meat in a large Dutch oven until meat is brown. Drain off grease.
Add sauce and mushrooms.
(Add your own special touches, onions, black olives, etc.)
Cook a few minutes.
Add spaghetti.
Pour mixture into two ungreased casseroles.
Cover and bake one in 375° oven, stirring occasionally, until spaghetti is tender, about 45 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with one cup of cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Freeze other casserole and bake another night.
If having a large crowd for dinner, bake both. Enjoy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given by hand.
When well blended, drop by tablespoon on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Great cookies.
The kids will love them. Easy for young cooks to make, under adult supervision.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Combine drained and flaked crab, parsley and pimento.
Blend together mustard, onion salt and mayonnaise.
Toss mixtures together.
Fill each crown with 2 tablespoons of the crab mixture.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until hot.

title: fried chicken with creamy gravy
directions: Rinse chicken pieces; pat dry with paper towels.
In a plastic bag combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Add a few chicken breasts at a time to the bag.
Shake to coat.
Remove chicken from bag, shaking of any excess coating in the bag.
Reserve remaining flour mixture.

title: mac beef and cheese
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Add 2/3 spaghetti sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine sauce mixture with macaroni. Pour into casserole; top with remaining spaghetti sauce.
Cut cheese slices diagonally.
Arrange around edge of casserole facing points toward center.
Bake on 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick with 3/4 cup water.
Add sausage and shredded cheese.
Shape into walnut sized balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on cookie sheets.
Freeze leftovers.
Reheat at 300° for 10 minutes or until warm.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream
together
butter,
shortening and sugar.
(Note: You may
use
1/2 cup of butter or 1/2 cup shortening in place of
1/4 each, if you prefer.) Add egg and beat together.
Sift flour
with baking soda, mix together well, adding the vanilla and
nuts. Divide
the
dough into four.
Roll each into long rectangle tubes, using wax paper.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Slice thin and bake on greased baking sheets, at 350° to 375° for ten minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar in a bowl.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Sift in flour, soda and salt.
Stir until blended.
Add chocolate.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Let stand, covered, until cool.

title: tomato-lentil delight
directions: Cook lentils, onion, carrot and celery together in 4 cups water for 1/2 hour.
Add other ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom only of 12 medium muffin cups.
Beat egg; stir in milk, oil and blueberries.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once.
Stir until flour is moist. (Batter will be lumpy.)
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Peel apples.
Layer potatoes and apples in a baking dish.
Dot with butter and pour syrup all over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: multi-nut brittle
directions: Butter a cookie sheet.
Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in a large saucepan.
Cook over high heat to 280° on candy thermometer.
Add nuts and cook, stirring, to 300° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla until blended.
Add baking soda and stir vigorously.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown ground meat and onion; drain.
Place in large pan.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours (if possible).
When served, top with shredded cheddar cheese and/or taco chips.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Lay ham out flat.
Slice cream cheese and press with fingers on the ham.
Put green onion to fit on cream cheese lengthwise. Roll up.
Slice into 1-inch circles.
Arrange on a serving plate.

title: roast pork loin
directions: Mix ingredients and rub thoroughly into the loin.
Roast at 325° for 4 to 5 hours, until tender.
After meat has baked for 1 1/2 hours, spread generously with topping.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture.
Cook in waffle iron for 1 minute.
Frost with chocolate frosting, if desired.

title: blueberry coffee cake(pretty and delicious)
directions: Combine sugar, butter and egg in mixing bowl; cream well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; add alternately to creamed mixture with milk.
Beat well; blend in blueberries. Spread dough in greased 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: corn soup
directions: Chop bacon and fry with onion. Drain and add corn, salt, and water. Reduce heat when corn breaks apart and cook 5 minutes. Add soup, then milk. Heat to serving temperature.

title: vienna tarts(kolachkee)
directions: Cream butter and cheese until blended and fluffy. Add flour and knead to smooth dough. Wrap and chill several hours. Roll 1/8-inch thick into a rectangle. Cut into 2-inch squares. Place 1/4 teaspoon tart grape jelly in center of each; fold corner over and seal together tightly. Brush with egg yolk mixed with milk. Sprinkle with ground nuts. Place on ungreased baking sheets and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: saucy asparagus
directions: Combine soup and milk in saucepan over medium heat until boiling, stirring frequently.
Add asparagus.
Cover pan and reduce heat to low.
Cook until asparagus is tender (about 10 min), stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: greasy bread
directions: Cook bacon or pork and reserve all the grease.
Spread liquid grease on rye bread, both sides, toast on grill.
Stack the veggies on the toasted bread, add salt and pepper to taste.
If bacon was used for grease, add it to the stack and cut as an open-faced sandwich.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Then stir in sugar.
Combine spices in pumpkin and fold in along with flour to first mixture. Spread onto a well-greased jelly roll sheet (15 x 10 x 1-inch). Top with one cup finely chopped walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Turn out onto towel. Roll up.
When cool, unroll and fill.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add vegetable oil and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk into egg mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Freezes well.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: hot percolator punch
directions: Mix and put the first 4 ingredients in a 36-cup electric coffeemaker.
Add in top basket the remaining ingredients.
Let perk in coffeemaker as coffee.

title: tortellini primavera
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms, onion and garlic in margarine in large skillet.
Add all remaining ingredients except tortellini, mix well.
Cook until mixture just begins to boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tortellini; cook until thoroughly heated. Makes 4 servings.

title: cast a spell over chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in margarine (melted); coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time:
5 minutes, cooking time:
25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Saute celery, onion, almonds and water chestnuts in butter. Mix rice, soup and mayo together in bowl.
Stir in the four ingredients that have been sauteed.
Add the cut up cooked chicken and cheese. Spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam and put mixture in pan. Top with crushed potato chips and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Enjoy!

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour in pie shell.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased pan (9 x 13-inches).
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread on batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Delicious served with whipped cream as a dessert.

title: basil chicken salad
directions: About 2 hours before or early in the day, mix vinegar, basil, sugar and 1/4 cup oil in a large bowl. Set aside.

title: nacho popcorn
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan; stir in paprika, red pepper and cumin. Let cool for 5 minutes.
Place popcorn in large bowl.
Pour mixture on top; sprinkle on cheese and toss popcorn until all is coated.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water together.
Add other ingredients. Put in dish and let chill overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, drain and mash.
Add all remaining ingredients except margarine and cracker crumbs.
Place ingredients in buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Top with crumbs and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May be frozen. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Top with second crust.
Crimp edges to seal; slit top crust.
Brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and serve.

title: chicken caesar salad
directions: Rinse tenders.
Cook chicken in dressing, oil and minced garlic over medium-high heat until done.
Make salad.

title: john's maple candy
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Roll into little balls the size of walnuts.
Refrigerate one to two hours.
(Best if made a day ahead of serving time.)
Also may be rolled in finely shredded coconut or chopped pecans and placed on waxed paper lined cookie sheets until chilled.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: crisco's super crisp country fried chicken
directions: Combine milk and egg in medium bowl.
Set aside.
Combine in plastic bag; flour, garlic salt, Paprika, black pepper, poultry seasoning.
Add
a few pieces of chicken at a time.
Shake to coat.
Dip chicken in milk-egg mixture.
Shake second time in flour mixture.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Rinse scallops and pat dry with paper towels.
Cook onion, celery and green pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add scallops.
Place half of the rice in a buttered 1 1/2-quart dish.
Cover with half of the scallop mixture and half of the cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: clam paste(dip)
directions: Soften cream cheese in a medium size mixing bowl at room temperature.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Serve with chips.

title: green bean special
directions: Combine sour cream and dressing; add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill 4-5 hours before serving.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Wash leeks and dice about 2 ounces of tender white hearts. Put aside.
Cut rest of leek into 1/2-inch pieces.
In pan, add water, potatoes, leeks and onion.
Bring to boil.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Remove potatoes and leeks.
Force through ricer or puree in blender.
Return to soup pot.
Add tender diced leeks, butter and cream.
Bring to boil.
Stir.
Do not allow to burn.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Stir in cheese and seasoning to taste.
Serve with crusty bread.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Stir all ingredients in pan with a fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously 1 minute.
Bake until toothpick, inserted in center, comes out clean.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run a knife or spatula around sides of loaf to loosen. Remove from pan.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Heat drippings; blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Gradually blend in broth and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in an 8 x 8 or a round pan at 400° for 1 hour. This is a delicious side dish.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Saute the minced bell pepper and onion in butter.
Add ground meat and other ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Core bell peppers; boil until tender.
Stuff with meat mixture.
Top with grated cheese, if desired.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: scampi
directions: Brown shrimp in oil.
Add vermouth, garlic, salt and pepper. Saute until liquid is nearly gone.
Sprinkle with parsley and lemon juice.
Serves 4.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut the ribs into serving pieces.
Mix all of the remaining ingredients in a saucepan and heat to boiling.
Pour sauce over meat.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Bake, covered, in a 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: frosted cashew cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Mix baking mix, brown sugar, sour cream, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Stir in cashews.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until no indentation remains when touched.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Select a melon with a thick rind.
Remove outer green skin and pink flesh; use only the greenish white parts of rind, cut in 1-inch cubes.
Combine water and lime.
Add cubed rind and soak overnight in refrigerator.
Drain and rinse cubes in cold water several times, then cover with cold water and boil for 30 minutes. Drain.

title: abby's pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into
a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over filling.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
You can top it with
a bit of whipped cream or ice cream; but even plain, nothing tops this!

title: chocolate chocolate-chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter an 8-inch square glass pan. Melt the butter and chocolate in the top of a double boiler and stir well. In a mixing bowl, combine butter and chocolate with sugar, flour, nuts, baking powder and vanilla.
Stir well. Add eggs and mix thoroughly. Stir in chocolate chips. Pour into pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together Spry, sugar and eggs; then add cocoa, sour milk and flour.
Last, add boiling water.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: smoothie chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: In 1-quart glass bowl, combine chocolate and milk. Micro-cook, covered, until chocolate melts, about 1 minute, stirring once.
Stir in sugar, vanilla and salt.
Fold in the nuts.

title: mexican meat and potatoes
directions: Brown stew meat in oil in a large pot. Cover meat with water and boil until tender. Add potatoes, onions, cumin, garlic salt, pepper and enough water to cover potatoes and onions. Cook until potatoes are done. Add stewed tomatoes. Let cook until thick like a stew.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Beat sugar, shortening and egg with wooden spoon until smooth and creamy.
Add cream of tartar, baking soda and salt and mix again.
Add flour gradually and mix well.
Form the dough into balls about 1-inch in diameter and roll each ball in mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 9 minutes at 400°. Makes about 36 cookies.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; beat in egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat vigorously; add flavoring.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan, greased and sprinkled with white sugar.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and peppers.
Mix in other ingredients. Refrigerate and serve.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Crush walnuts fine, melt butter and mix flour all together. Press firmly in 9x13 pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°,

title: crab dip
directions: Rub bowl with cut garlic.
Gradually add cream to cream cheese; blend until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Chill.
Serve with unsalted crackers.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix together the pudding, 3 cups milk and Cool Whip.
In a pot, mix the margarine (melted).
Add the sugar, cocoa, 1/4 cup milk and vanilla. Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Layer pudding mix, graham crackers, pudding mix and top with chocolate mixture.

title: corn and lima beans succotash
directions: Boil broth; add lima beans and corn.
Cover and cook 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add pepper and sugar; cook for 4 minutes, until you only have a little broth left.
Stir in sour cream.
Place in bowl and serve.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This is a good recipe for cheaper cuts of steak.
Also goes well on chicken or ground beef.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Brown chops.
In casserole mix soup, milk and water.
Put browned chops into mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes. Good served with rice.

title: rich sweet dough
directions: Scald milk and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm, add sugar and salt, add yeast mixture, eggs and flour.
Stir until stiff enough dough to knead.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down. Shape into loaves and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Dough can be refrigerated for 3 days.

title: beer venison chops
directions: Brown chops in bacon grease and pour off fat.
Blend brown sugar, catsup and beer.
Pour over chops.
Cook in an electric frypan until tender, about 1 hour (may need to add a little water as it cooks down).
Spoon sauce over chops and serve.

title: orange (tang) salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice with Tang and pudding mix.
Mix fruits together and fold into pudding mixture.
Chill.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes coarsely in processor or blender.
Add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 1/2 package cream cheese, 1/4 cup mayonnaise, 1/4 teaspoon dill weed, garlic and lemon juice.
Process until smooth. Smooth into 10-inch pie plate.
Process the balance of ingredients until smooth and add to plate.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and keep juice.
To juice add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Flake salmon and combine all ingredients.
Pack into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: codfish cakes (marinade)
directions: Soak codfish in cold water overnight; discard water.
Boil 1 quart of water; drop codfish in water.
Turn fire off; let stand 10 minutes.
Discard water.
Cool and shred cod.
Mix egg with 1 1/2 cups water and milk; pour over flour mixture and gradually make a soft paste.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop 1 tablespoon at a time in hot oil (deep fry).
Very good as an appetizer.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, chopped onions and green pepper. Saute until soft. Drain off half the grease. Brown hamburger.
Mix together remaining ingredients. Bake in greased casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat powdered sugar, cream cheese and eggs for 5 minutes.
Pour over mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese, garlic powder and pepper; add broccoli and carrot.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Cover; cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Add spaghetti.
Heat through.
Serves 3 to 4.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: elegant seafood crepes
directions: *You may substitute other fresh seafoods.

title: quick and easy yeast bread
directions: Mix together 2 cups flour, sugar and salt.
Warm milk and water to 120°.
Add yeast to milk mixture.
Add liquid yeast mixture to dry ingredients.
Add butter and eggs.
Add remaining flour until correct consistency.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Let rest to double in a warm place (about 20 minutes).
Punch down; divide and shape.
Place in loaf pans.
Let rise again.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: saltwater taffy
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, water, syrup, salt and cocoa.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Continue to cook to hard ball stage (260°), without stirring, about 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and flavorings.
Pour into buttered 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Cool until comfortable to handle, 10 to 15 minutes.
Butter hands lightly; gather small amounts of taffy into a ball and pull until candy becomes opaque and holds its shape.
Pull each piece into a long strand about 1/2-inch thick.
With buttered kitchen shears, snip into bite size pieces.
Wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Put Ritz crackers in food processor.
Put crushed crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted butter over top.
Combine together (make sure all crumbs have butter on them).
Flatten out evenly on bottom of pan.

title: chicken with apple cream sauce
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper. In a large skillet over medium-high heat, cook chicken in hot oil until browned on each side. Add juice concentrate, lemon juice and rosemary. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until juices of chicken run clear.
Remove chicken, but keep warm.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour in greased pan at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.
Prick top of loaf when baked.

title: fabulous fried onion rings
directions: Combine flour and beer thoroughly with whisk in large bowl. Cover bowl and let set at room temperature for at least 3 hours. Cut onions into slices and separate into rings.
Stir into batter, then fry in oil at 375°.
(An electric skillet works best.)
Turn once or twice until golden, then transfer them to a preheated 200° oven, layering on brown paper bags or paper towels on cookie sheet.
These stay crispy and crunchy for hours so you can make ahead and clean up the mess.
They freeze and reheat well, too, if you have any left!

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers.
Slice cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Let come to a boil in the solution.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until hot through.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Makes 7 pints.

title: onion and cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Cover with salt.
Press with heavy object for 30 minutes.
Pour off water.
Mix sour cream and vinegar and pour over.
Serve.

title: butterscotch fingers
directions: Place butterscotch bits and milk in double boiler.
After bits are melted, boil 8 to 10 minutes, then pour milk over Rice Chex and nuts; stir until coated.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: best ever oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the sugars, oil and eggs in a very large bowl (I use a 10-quart bowl for plenty of stirring space).
Combine soda, baking powder, salt and flour and add to the sugar mixture.
Stir in the oats, chocolate chips, coconut and cereal.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix the oil, eggs and sugar together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Grease muffin tin and fill 2/3 full. Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: salmon egg salad sandwich filling
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly, but well.
Yields 8 sandwiches.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Let margarine and grated cheese come to room temperature, then mix. Add flour, salt and onion soup mix. Mix together and divide into 4 rolls. Roll each one in foil and freeze. Slice thin and bake in a 400° oven. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes. Yield: 5 dozen.

title: crescents
directions: Soften butter; add nuts.
Mix in sugar, gradually add flour; take small amount of dough, roll in hand and form crescent shapes. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Roll in superfine sugar.

title: rotel chicken
directions: In large bowl combine chicken, onion, pepers and soup.
In greased 9x13 pan spread doritos in the bottom.
Spread chicken mix over top.
Pour 1 can of rotel over top, cover with velveeta slices and add other can of rotel.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef and eggs well; add bread crumbs, salt and pepper thoroughly.
Add in ketchup, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Shape into meat loaf.
Pour very little ketchup over top for extra flavor.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until desired tenderness.

title: wendy's style chili
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Break meat into tiny pieces. Place soup and 1/2 meat into blender.
Process on high until it resembles cement mortar.
Place with unblended meat into 2 1/2-quart pan.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until flavors are blended.

title: old fashioned cocoa cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Beat first the flour ingredients at high speed of mixer 3 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with water to creamed mixture. Blend just until combined.
Add candy.
Pour into two greased and cocoa dusted cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: carolyn's blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in oblong Pyrex pan. In bowl, mix flour, sugar and milk.
Stir mixture in melted margarine.
Add blueberries to mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder, salt and soda together.
Add to mixture and blend thoroughly.
Mix in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sydnie's green pepper steak
directions: Allow steak to soak in ginger, garlic and soy sauce. Heat oil until hot. Cook steak in oil until brown. Turn heat to low and simmer steak 25 to 30 minutes. Add green onions and green pepper. Cook on high 10 minutes. Mix cornstarch with water. Add to steak and vegetables. Add the tomato. Let set for 10 minutes. Serve with white rice.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix all except dates, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° until brown on top (don't overbake).
Makes about 40.

title: creamed dried beef
directions: Cook beef with butter in 10-inch skillet on medium for 3 minutes or until edges curl.
Gradually stir in flour.
Add milk all at once.
Stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Add Worcestershire sauce and pepper to taste. Spoon over buttered toast.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: cranberry frozen salad
directions: Hand mix well.
Line muffin tin with paper liners.
Pour mixture into muffin cups.
Freeze until firm.
Store in Ziploc freezer bags.
Thaw slightly before serving.
Serves 12.

title: lite & easy crustless pumpkin pie(low calorie)
directions: In medium bowl, sprinkle gelatin over cold water to soften. In a small saucepan, heat 1 cup of the evaporated Low Fat milk just to boiling.
Slowly stir hot milk into gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Mix in remaining milk, the pumpkin, brown sugar, pumpkin pie spice and vanilla.
Set aside.
Spray 10 inch glass pie plate with non-stick vegetable spray.
Pour mixture into pie plate, chill until firm.

title: chiles rellenos casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet, stirring to crumble beef; drain well.
Stir in 1/2 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper, and set aside.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix all and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until the mixture comes to a boil.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.
Serve over gingerbread, angel food, etc.

title: sparkling holiday punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add pineapple juice. Pour into punch bowl over a piece of ice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 1 gallon or 32 punch cups.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper until crisp-tender; do not brown.
Add soups, Cheez Whiz, mushrooms and pimentos.
Mix until well blended.
Add chicken pieces and noodles.
Pour into three-quart casserole.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar on top.
Bake at 350° until center begins to bubble.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Add dry jello.
Cool completely.
Slice strawberries and fold into jello mixture.
Put in favorite pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Makes two pies.

title: five can casserole
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Place noodles in bottom of dish, then layer of meat, 1st can of soup, layer of meat, 2nd can of soup, then ditto 3rd and 4th cans of soup with layer of meat.
Pour Pet milk plus 1 can of water over mixture.
Cover with grated cheese. Bake about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; mix well.
Add egg and mix well. Add milk slowly and blend well.
Start cooking on high heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce to medium heat, stirring constantly. After thickened, add vanilla.
Blend well.
Serve hot or cold.

title: curried fruit
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add sugar and curry powder.
Add pineapple and syrup to skillet.
Mix and simmer until sugar is melted.
Put fruits in a buttered shallow pan or baking dish (1 1/2-quart).
Pour sauce over fruit.
Bake 1 hour. Makes 8 servings.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor bowl.
Pulse to blend and then run continuous for 10 to 15 seconds.
Makes 1 cup.

title: minute fudge frosting
directions: Stir over low heat until shortening and chocolate melts. Bring to full rolling boil; stir constantly.
Boil 1 minute, remove from heat and beat until lukewarm.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and spread over any cooled cake.

title: my mother-in-law's cheese custard
directions: Blend all but egg whites and brown sugar.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Mix the m.s.g., soy sauce and ginger; set aside.
Add chicken cube to water to make broth; set aside.
Heat oil; saute steak and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add m.s.g. mix, chicken broth and broccoli pieces.
Put cover on pan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch, which was diluted.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water until dissolved. Add sherbet, stirring well.
Let set in refrigerator until thick. Add oranges and whipped cream.
Chill.

title: yummy yams
directions: Alternate layers of yams and banana slices in a 1-quart casserole ending with a layer of yams.
Melt margarine.
Stir in salt, corn syrup and orange juice.
Pour over yams and bananas. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Baste yams and bananas with liquid.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes or until coconut is browned.

title: strawberry banana soup
directions: Combine strawberries, banana and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Blend sugar.
Mix sour cream and rest of sugar; whip and blend into milk and sour cream.
