Add wine.
Whisk until well blended; fold in strawberries and bananas.
Chill 2 hours.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut each medium size potato into about six pieces.
Place in a baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and sausage with hands until well blended.
Mix in cheese and roll into walnut-sized balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir in buttermilk until mix is a medium batter.
Drop into cooking oil and deep fry until golden brown.

title: pork poor boy
directions: Rub roast with pepper; place in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast uncovered at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes; slice thin.
Slice bread lengthwise.
On bottom half of bread, layer spinach, meat, tomato, cucumber, avocado, green pepper and alfalfa sprouts.
Drizzle with dressing.
Replace top of bread and serve immediately.

title: cindy's baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch squares.
Fry and remove from skillet to drain.
Place onion (chopped) into skillet with bacon grease. Cook until clear; add pork and beans (remove pork fat).
Add sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce to taste.

title: curried fruit
directions: Saute curry powder in butter.
Add sugar.
Arrange fruit in baking dish in layers, placing some sugar mixture between each layer.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Baste with mixture and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: rose jar potpourri(makes 1 jar)
directions: Add 7/8 cup water.
Knead dough about 10 minutes after mixing thoroughly.
If dough is sticky, add a little more flour.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in shapes with cookie cutters or shape freehand.
Make coils, balls, etc. for trim to decorate.
Moisten to stick to dough.
Bake about an hour at 325°.
Paint with water colors or food color.
Make a hole with a straw before baking if you want to hang on the tree.

title: "patricia's" broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw and squeeze out excess liquid from broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
It is done when toothpick put in center comes out clean.
Rub top with 3 or 4 pats of margarine as soon as it comes out of oven.

title: turkey sloppy joes
directions: Cook turkey; drain off any liquid.
Add the chopped vegetables and the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wilt a little onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add pepper and oleo.
If you like cheese, add a little.
Boil squash in salt water.
When done, drain water and mash.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole with a few cracker crumbs on top.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine/ butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated. Using buttered spatula, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cut into squares when cool.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, beat well.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to first ingredients by hand.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallows over cake.
Bake 10 more minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool completely.
Ice.

title: stewed eggplant
directions: Wash, peel and cut eggplant into small pieces.
Cut onion and bell pepper into small pieces.
Enough water to cover; salt to taste.
Stew down until tender or most of water is gone.

title: spanish style green beans
directions: Remove strings from beans; wash beans thoroughly. Cut beans into 1 1/2 inch pieces. Cook beans in boiling salted water 15 to 20 minutes or until crisp tender. Drain and set aside.
Saute green pepper and onion in hot oil until tender. Add tomatoes, basil, rosemary, salt, pepper, and beans, mixing well. Heat thoroughly.

title: mother cade's apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
After sifting flour, measure and then add spices, cocoa and a pinch of salt.
Dissolve soda in water.
Add nuts and apples last.
Cook in a slow oven at 350° in a greased and floured pan.

title: fettucine
directions: Combine garlic and olive oil.
Cream butter and add to oil mixture.
Combine egg yolks and cream to oil mixture.
Boil fettucine noodles; drain well.
Add mixture to noodles.
Add salt and pepper.

title: peanut butter crunch cake
directions: Beat cake mix, brown sugar and peanut butter in bowl until crumbly. Reserve 2/3 cup.
Beat remaining mixture, water, oil and eggs.
Pour into pan.
Stir nuts into reserved crumbly mixture. Sprinkle over batter. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: one-step coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a large bowl (or blender) and blend well.
Pour into a buttered 10-inch pie plate and bake in a preheated oven for about 1 hour.
When done, the crust will be on the bottom, the custard in the middle and the coconut on top.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and press graham cracker crumbs and butter into bottom and up sides of pan.

title: honey nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake bread until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then place on a wire rack.
Cool completely.
Slice and serve.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to cream mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 9 minutes in 350° oven.

title: collard greens
directions: Wash greens and cut them.
Place ham hocks in boiler with about 1 quart of water and let boil about 30 minutes.
Then add oil, salt and sugar.
Add greens and cook over medium heat.
Stir about every 10 minutes and cook until tender.

title: broccoli parmesan fettuccine
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water with a cover for about 3 minutes; drain and plunge into ice water. Drain and set aside. Cook fettuccine according to directions; drain and place in a large bowl. Set aside.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugars together. Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in rolled oats.
Fold in gumdrops and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: lemon chicken with thyme
directions: In a plastic/paper bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.

Shake to mix. Add chicken and shake to coat lightly. Remove chicken and reserve excess seasoned flour. In large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil over medium heat. Add chicken and brown on one side, about 5 minutes. Add other tablespoon oil; turn chicken and brown on second side.

Transfer chicken to a plate; set aside. Add margarine to skillet; melt and cook onions, stirring until softened, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in remaining seasoned flour; cook, stirring, about 1 minute. Add chicken broth, 2 tablespoons lemon juice and thyme. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly. Return chicken to skillet; reduce heat and cover. Cook chicken about 5 minutes. Remove chicken. Stir in remaining 1 tablespoon lemon juice into sauce. Stir and pour over chicken. Serve chicken with lemon wedges and a sprinkling of parsley.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cook and stir milk and flour together until thick.
Let it cool until cold.
Add butter, Crisco, sugar, salt and vanilla; mix with flour mixture and beat at least 10 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator until cake is done and cold, then frost.

title: miracle rugalah dough
directions: This dough will do anything where a pastry dough is needed. It can be used for a dessert, canapes, pie crust and etc.
Keep a supply in the freezer at all times.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Put broccoli, pieces of chicken (whole or cubed, your choice) in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup and half and half together.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: christmas nuts
directions: Beat egg white with cold water; beat until foamy.
Stir in nuts and mix well until nuts are completely coated.
Mix in bowl the brown and white sugars, nutmeg, salt and cinnamon.
Pour over nut mixture and stir until nuts are covered.
Pour on cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir 3 or 4 times while baking.

title: turtle cake(caramel chocolate brownies)
directions: Put caramels in top of double boiler with the 1/3 cup of milk.
Put cake mix in a bowl with margarine, milk and nuts. Combine into stuff dough.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix and pour over the above.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Let sit 15 minutes before serving.

title: brisket with parsley sauce
directions: Sear brisket in oil in a big pot (with a lid), browning both sides.
When brown, remove to a platter.
Add vegetables, garlic and pepper; saute until vegetables start to brown.
Return meat to pot, laying on top of vegetables.
Add water or broth until about half of meat is covered.
Cover pot tightly and cook on top of stove at slow simmer 2 1/2 hours (or in 325° oven) until a fork pierces meat easily.
Allow to cool in its juices overnight. Pour off all juice into a container and place in freezer until fat congeals and can be removed.
Return defatted sauce to meat. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: harvey house slaw
directions: In large bowl, make layers of cabbage, green pepper and onions. Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over top.

title: creole stuffed peppers
directions: Boil peppers (opened from top and cleaned) for 5 minutes in salted water.
Combine meat, 1/4 cup onion, celery, salt, egg and milk.
Drain peppers and stuff with meat mixture.
Place in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: venezuela rice salad
directions: Cook rice
according
to
package
directions and cool. While it is
still warm, add chopped onion, vinegar, corn oil, curry powder and	salt.
Chill
for
3 hours or overnight. Add chopped celery, peas
which
have
been
cooked and cooled and mayonnaise. Add chicken
pieces
or
chopped
boiled eggs, although the salad is	delicious even without it. Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: easy noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Boil egg noodles until tender.
Using a casserole dish, layer noodles, beef, sauce and cheese.
Bake until cheese is bubbly at 450°.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: In one pot, start cooking cut-up chicken in water. In heavy skillet, make roux (1 cup oil, 1 cup flour). Cook until dark brown, stirring constantly. Over medium flame, add chopped onion, celery and garlic; cook slowly, still stirring, until very tender. Will make a thick gravy. Add roux mixture to chicken; cook till tender, then add okra, stewed tomatoes, green onions and parsley. Cook 20 minutes.
Serve over rice. Oysters or shrimp may be added if desired.

title: frank-bean bake
directions: Heat oven
to
Mix beans, spaghetti sauce, onion and cheese
in	an
ungreased
1 1/2 quart casserole.
Arrange frankfurters on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until bean mixture is bubbly and frankfurters are light brown.

title: easy macaroni meal
directions: Brown ground beef in a pan sprayed with Pam.
Add tomato juice and seasonings.
Cook over low heat.
When mixture is boiling about 5 minutes, gradually add the macaroni so that the tomato juice mixture continues to boil.
Add green peppers and onion.
Cover and cook until macaroni is tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally during cooking.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, then add the eggs one at a time, beating well.
Stir in pineapple and fold in the bread cubes.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: wild rice
directions: Rinse the rice.
Place all ingredients together in a pot (with a tight lid).
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 45 minutes, keeping lid on tight.
Remove from heat and set aside, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir with a fork to fluff. Serves 4 to 6.

title: paula's potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on.
Peel as soon as possible.
Mash up.
Add the Italian seasoning.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 425° in unbaked pie shell for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Cook until knife blade comes out clean.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Mix mashed sweet potatoes, oleo, sugar, vanilla, eggs and milk together. Put in 9 x 12-inch greased pan.

title: purple poke cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Poke holes in cake with knife at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add cold water and pour over cake in pan. Chill 3 to 4 hours and top with Cool Whip. Store in refrigerator.

title: layered taco bean dip
directions: In a large bowl, combine the bean dip and taco mix.
Spread mixture in a 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle chopped onions over mixture.
Blend together Miracle Whip and sour cream.
Spread over onions.
Sprinkle sliced ripe olives on top.
Chill.
Serve with corn chips.

title: kiss of lemon pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In blender heat oats 1 minute.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs and lemon peel; mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternating with milk, mixing until blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake, hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
In a blender, blend raspberries until smooth.
Serve with pound cake.
Makes 16 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, peanuts, Karo syrup and salt.
Microwave on High heat for 4 minutes.
Take out; stir well.
Put back in microwave 4 more minutes.
Remove.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon butter.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Take out.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir.
Pour on a greased cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: chocolate fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonfat cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine apple butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and egg substitute and mix until blended smooth.
Stir in cocoa, flour and baking powder.
Mix until all ingredients are blended.
Spoon batter into prepared dish and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Makes 24 brownies.

title: cinnamon apple dessert
directions: Slice apples and place in an 8 x 8-inch square, greased baking dish.
Add raisins, nuts and brown sugar.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add egg. Stir with fork until mixture forms balls.
Spread over apple mixture evenly.
Pour butter evenly over apple mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except sugar/cinnamon and raisins.
Cut into shapes, fancy or round.
Bake until just done, approximately 12 minutes at 350°.

title: green chili rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in hot butter until clear. Remove from heat and stir in hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly to mix.

title: quick curried shrimp
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and microwave at High for 11 to 13 minutes or until bubbly, stirring every 4 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yields 6 servings. Preparation time is about 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball 1
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese thoroughly.
Chop ends of green onions up and add to mixture.
Form ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: imperial salad freeze
directions: Mash bananas.
Stir in other ingredients.
Put into ring mold or Bundt cake pan or paper filled cupcake pans.
Freeze well overnight or all day.
Remove from freezer about serving time.

title: aunt lula's awful good pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Cream together butter, sugar and egg yolks. Add raisins and pecans.
Add vinegar and vanilla, mixing well. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Put in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Chop tomatoes fine; drain off juice.
Add same amount of water and scald.
Pour off.
Scald in same amount of water again. Drain, then add apples (chopped fine), sugar, raisins, suet, salt and vinegar.
Cook until tomatoes are color of raisins.
When cool, add spices.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in macaroni, juice, onions and spices.
Bring to a boil and set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomato mixture and ground beef into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered.
Add shredded cheese and return to oven for 10 minutes.
Use whatever type of cheese your family likes.
This is a great one dish meal.

title: cold ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, crumbs, potatoes, eggs and parsley.
Saute onion in butter; stir in mustard, salt and pepper.
Add to ham mixture. Rinse
a
bread pan in cold water;
pack ham mixture into it. Turn out ham loaf onto a greased shallow baking pan. Mix
orange juice
concentrate
and
honey;
brush over loaf. Bake
at 400° for 20 minutes.
Brush with rest of orange juice mixture
and bake 20 minutes more.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Blend flour, salt and vanilla into mixture and beat well.
Add eggs, then stir milk into mixture.
Line two 9-inch pans with pie crust.
Pour in the filling and bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for another 30 minutes or until filling is firm.
(I use 1 cup whole pecans or chopped pecans in bottom of crust.)

title: terry's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs.
Mix salt and baking soda into flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.
(Remove from oven when only starting to brown, cookies will be soft.)
If you let them brown completely, they will be hard.
Please do not substitute margarine or butter for the shortening.
It will change the texture.
These are also great with butterscotch or peanut butter chips.
Enjoy!

title: mexican wieners
directions: Cut hot dogs in small chunks.
Boil hot dogs until heated through.
Combine hot dogs and salsa.
Stir to coat.
May use stove top or crock-pot.
Heat until ready to use.

title: 4-day coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix per directions on box.
Let stand 15 minutes. Cut the two layers in half to make 4 layers.
Dental floss works great for cutting the layers.

title: karo-nut pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar and sift.
Add melted oleo, 3 beaten eggs, salt and Karo.
Mix all together; beat well and add the pecans. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheddar meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine ground beef, oatmeal, onion and seasonings. Blend in eggs and milk.
Add cheese; mix carefully.
Shape into shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yummy!

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, chilies, onion, Cheddar cheese and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread onto tortillas sparingly.
Roll up.
Cover and chill for 2 hours or overnight.
Keep tightly covered.

title: apple 'n cheese casserole
directions: Place apples in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add the flour; mix.
Press the creamed mixture into the apples.
Spread and press grated cheese into the mixture in dish.
Pour milk/cream on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each. Add dry ingredients, then fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 days. Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: zucchini and rice boats
directions: Cut a thin slice lengthwise from zucchini; hollow out using a grapefruit knife.
Chop zucchini meat.
Parboil zucchini shells about 5 minutes; drain on paper towels.

title: fresh corn fritters
directions: Preheat oil in a deep fryer to 375 degrees. Combine the buttermilk and Tabasco.
Mix well.
In another bowl, combine the corn meal mix, flour and Essence.
Stir to mix. Add corn and buttermilk mixture to the dry ingredients.
Mix well. Drop from a tablespoon into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes about 2 dozen small fritters or 18 medium size fritters.

title: baked chicken mexican style
directions: In a pie plate, beat eggs and salsa.
On a sheet of wax paper, combine the bread crumbs and spices.
Dip each chicken piece in the egg mixture and roll in crumbs, then dip again in egg mixture and again in crumbs.
Set aside.

title: peach pudding
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, then mix peaches, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup of water.
Dot with butter.
Pour the butter over this and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef or pork roast in french dip
directions: Wash the roast and place in a crock-pot.
Mix the remaining ingredients in 2 1/2 cups water and pour over roast.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Take meat out and shred.
Put meat in individual French rolls.
Put the juice in soup or salad bowls; use as a dip for the sandwiches.

title: ham and cheese appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread in greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into rectangles.

title: hawaiian sandwiches(method:  foil)
directions: Start with roll.
Add cheese, ham, pineapple, ham and cheese. Wrap in foil and bake in fire.

title: berry patch blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix cornstarch and sugar in saucepan. Stir in the water.
Bring to boil, stirring, and cook for 1 minute or until mixture is somewhat clear.
Add blueberries and pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish or 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 1 teaspoon of oil.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine milk and remaining oil and add all at once to flour mix.
Stir until it forms a ball (or use processor).
Drop by spoonfuls into fruit.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot or warm with cream or ice cream.

title: "quick" texas cake
directions: Beat eggs and pie filling until cherries are smooth.
Add the cake mix; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cook, covered, in boiling water just until tender, about 35 minutes.
Drain, peel and place in a large bowl. While potatoes are still warm, mash with an electric mixer.
Add butter, bourbon, orange juice, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Turn mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.
(May be made ahead up to this point.
Cover and chill until ready to bake.)
Sprinkle nuts around the edge to make a border.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until lightly browned. Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cocoa and cornstarch or flour until well blended, set aside.
Heat milk just till hot, add sugar mixture and bring to a boil in a heavy saucepan, stirring constantly. Beat egg yolks and add about 1/2 of hot mix while stirring.
Add back to hot custard in sauce pan while stirring.
Heat until boils again.
Stir in butter and vanilla and cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: anise almond cookies
directions: Lightly butter cookie sheet.
Mix flour, baking powder, butter, eggs and sugar.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, sherry and anise seed, mixing well.
Fold in almonds; knead and form into 2 rolls 12-inches long x 2-inches wide.
Transfer rolls to prepared cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove and cut diagonally while still hot.
Replace in oven 10 minutes to dry out.
Remove and cool.

title: peanut butter bars cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, oil and egg in bowl with spoon until smooth.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Divide dough in half. Shape one half into two strips about 15 x 1 1/2-inches and about 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten strip to 3-inches wide with fork dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake for 6 to 7 minutes for soft cookies or 8 to 9 minutes for crisp cookies. Cool 2 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining half of dough.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost spinach and squeeze.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients and put in hollowed bread center.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: If using cake mix, prepare as directed on box.
Dice cake in 1/2-inch cubes.
Put into a small punch, trifle or just a clear bowl.
Layer pineapple over cake.
Mix pudding and pour over pineapple before it sets.
Layer the pie filling over the pudding and top with the whipped topping.
Garnish with cherries and pecans.
This is also good with cherry pie filling and chocolate or vanilla pudding.
Leave out the pineapple, though.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Stir well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Toss gently. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Wash and cap strawberries.
Place in heavy Dutch oven.
Add vinegar; stir.
Boil 1 minute covered.
Uncover and add sugar; boil 20 minutes or more depending on type of berries.
Let set until completely cool or overnight.
Put into regular jars and seal.
Store in freezer or process in water bath for 5 minutes. They will stay brighter in freezer.

title: banana cake bread
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Add banana, flour and nuts.
Mix together.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes to 1 hour until done.
Yields 12 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Wash and core lettuce and tear into large bowl.
Cut up celery, approximately 1 to 2 cups on top of lettuce.
Chop green onions on top of celery (approximately 3 bunches).
Spread peas on top of green onions.
Spread mayonnaise over greens (approximately 1 cup), then cheese.
Add Bac*Os last.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: oven cooked chitterlings
directions: Lay chitterlings on heavy-duty foil.
On top, place onion, pepper and other seasonings.
Wrap in foil very tightly, making sure ends are tightly closed.
Put 2 inches of water in a roasting pan.
Put foil wrapped chitterlings in pan.
Cover well; bake in 350° oven for 3 hours.
Check water level in pan; if low, add 2 more inches.
Bake 2 hours more (total of 5 hours).

title: gene's ribs
directions: Salt and pepper ribs.
Cook ribs on grill until golden brown.

title: cooked smoked ham
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot.
Add water to cover ham butt.
Bring to boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Let cool in water, then remove, slice and serve.
Great hot or cold!

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain. Add water, onion, tomatoes, bouillon cubes and spices. Let cook until onions are almost tender. Add cabbage and beans and cook until tender.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Pick chicken from bone and mix with soup and sour cream. Place in a casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and put on chicken mixture.
Put almonds on top of crackers.
Melt margarine and pour over all.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned and bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: caramelized onions
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet; saute onions until golden brown. Sprinkle on sugar and continue to saute until onions are well browned and crisp.
Drain on paper towel to remove excess oil; set aside.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Brush chicken with 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Place flour and chicken in plastic bag and shake to cover chicken.
Arrange in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes. Combine remaining oleo, honey, lemon juice and soy sauce in small saucepan.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over partially cooked chicken. Bake for 30 more minutes.
Baste frequently.
Serves 6.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off grease.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in crock-pot; cut up Velveeta cheese and add to crock-pot.
Then stir in Ro-Tel sauce. Heat on low until cheese is all melted.
Keep hot in crock-pot and serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover with chili.
Top with shredded cheeses to cover chili.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts (30 minutes).
Stir before serving. Serve with Doritos.

title: orange nut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and part of the flour, then the milk, the rest of the flour and 1/2 cup pecans.
Bake in layers.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain and stir in salt. Spread in greased 9-inch pie plate and sprinkle with cheese. Stir milk, Bisquick and eggs together with fork until blended. Pour into plate. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Yield:
8 servings.

title: lemon chiffon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt into bowl.
Make well in center.
Add oil, egg yolks, 3/4 cup cold water, vanilla and lemon rind.
Beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form (do not underbeat).
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over egg whites; fold gently until blended.
Do not overmix.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt the Hershey in double boiler.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Put in crust.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Layer half the cake on bottom of a deep bowl.
Cover with half the prepared chocolate pudding.
Cover with half of chocolate bar, broken into small pieces.
Next, cover with one container of Cool Whip.
Repeat all layers.
Sprinkle chocolate on top with a cherry.
Refrigerate.

title: coffee "azuki" jello
directions: Mix and soften gelatine in cold coffee. Add hot coffee. Stir until dissolved. Add the tsubushi an and condensed milk. Pour into 9 x 9 pan. Refrigerate until set. Cut into squares.

title: nana's quick cake
directions: Cut angel food cake in 3 layers.
Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk and lemonade.
Let strawberries thaw.
Spread 1 layer with 1/4 Cool Whip mixture, then some strawberries.
Top with second layer, Cool Whip and strawberries.
Top with last layer and spread sides and top with Cool Whip mixture.
Save any leftover strawberries and when ready to serve, place on top of cake.
For best results, let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: braunschweiger roll(german liver sausage)
directions: Blend sausage and 1/3 of the cream cheese together, add rest of ingredients.
Mold into ball on foil-lined bowl, put into icebox overnight.
Mix rest of cream cheese and a little sour cream.
Use this to frost the ball.
Then roll the ball in crushed nuts or parsley.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, butter and chopped pecans for crumbs; set aside 1 1/2 cups.
Press remaining crumbs in pan.
Spread preserves to within 1 to 1 1/2 inches of pan.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pecan goodies
directions: Mix egg whites, sugar, vanilla and salt together.
Stir in pecans until pecans are coated.
Lay on cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 275°.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip together.
Stir until well mixed. Add pineapple, juice and all, marshmallows and nuts.
At Christmas time, put red and green cherries on top.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine biscuit mix, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Mix egg, milk, oil and pumpkin.
Sir into dry ingredients just until well blended.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 20 minutes or until done.

title: grandma lucy's baked beans(serves 10 to 12)
directions: In a large heavy skillet, brown bacon.
Remove bacon.
Add onion to grease in the pan.
Saute onion until soft.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: turkey quiche(for men!)
directions: Layer as listed first 4 ingredients.
Bring the soup and milk to boil.
Add eggs, slowly.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is firm.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: dad and bobbie's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 32 ounces.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine and heat until sugar dissolves. Pour over beans and stir gently. Refrigerate overnight, if possible. Good as long as it lasts.

title: penne pasta bake
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. Drain off fat. Cook pasta in large saucepan; drain and return to pan. Add ground beef, spaghetti sauce, and 1/2 parmesan cheese. Mix well and pour into ungreased 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Top with 1/4 cup parmesan cheese and 2 cups mozzarella cheese. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and water in a heavy pan.
Mix thoroughly.
Boil until mixture is cooked in fine pieces and onions are nearly done.
Add pepper, salt, chili powder and red peppers.
Let simmer until cooked nearly dry.
Add tomato juice and boil until desired thickness.

title: dessert tonight
directions: In a big bowl, add sugar and water.
Add 1 teaspoon of almond flavoring.
Mix and add 10 ice cubes.
Mix and serve.
May want to crush ice in blender.

title: original german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate; set aside.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Beat in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour batter into 3 (9-inch) layer pans, lined on bottoms with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed in center.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Spread frosting between layers and over top of cake.

title: missouri steak
directions: Cut round steak as desired.
Put in pan.
Slice layer of potatoes on top of steak, then slice layer of onions on potatoes. Cut peppers and cover onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour tomato juice over, enough to cover.
Bake in oven at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.
Yummy!

title: texas cowboy chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add black pepper, chili powder and hot sauce to taste.
Add jalapeno peppers, tomatoes and beans. Let everything simmer about 15 minutes, then add cheese.
It will take about 15 minutes to melt if its cut into pieces.
Serve with hard rolls.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown round steak (cut in 1-inch cubes) in 2 tablespoons oil. Add next 9 ingredients.
Add 2 cups hot water and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Cut skinless and boneless breasts into cubes.
Dice onions and saute in 1 stick oleo.
Then add paprika to onions and mix until all are an orange color.
Add chicken and salt and pepper to taste.
Then add enough chicken broth to just cover the chicken. Add 4 bouillon cubes.
Let simmer about 30 or 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
When chicken is done, add the sour cream and stir slowly.
Let simmer for 5 more minutes.
Cook packaged dumplings in salted water.
Add to chicken and blend.
At this time, also stir in another 1/2 stick oleo.

title: chicken el rancho
directions: Dip chicken breasts into a bowl of Ranch dressing; coat generously.
Then dip the chicken in bread crumbs.
Place on a cookie sheet (or other cooking pan of your choice) and bake for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on breast size.
It's quick, it's easy and it tastes great!
Serves 4.

title: ground meat casserole - t.v. channel 40
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper together.
Add tomato paste and corn.
Mix with Kraft dinner.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until hot.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic lightly in salad oil in a large skillet; push to one side.
Brown beef in same skillet.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, chili, salt, hot sauce and chili powder; heat to boiling.
Line pan with part of the tortillas.
Cover with about 1/3 of the sauce.
Continue to layer tortillas and sauce until used up.
Cover with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes. Serve bubbling hot.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon and salt.
Add other ingredients with nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oven "fried" potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Peel potatoes and cut lengthwise in small strips.
Dry with paper towels and place on cookie sheets that have been sprayed with Pam; do not overlap.
Spray tops of potatoes.
Bake potato strips for 1 hour, turning at 15 minute intervals.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: brussels sprouts with bacon
directions: Trim the bottoms of the Brussels sprouts and pull off any withered leaves. Cook them in boiling salted water until tender, about 10 minutes; drain. Cut the bacon into 1-inch pieces and fry until crisp. Drain on paper towels. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the fat from the pan. Add the vinegar to the pan and cook 1 minute over medium-high heat, scraping up the browned bits in the bottom of the pan. Add the Brussels sprouts and toss until warm. Sprinkle with bacon.

title: friendship tea
directions: Store all ingredients dry in airtight container.
To serve, place 1 1/2 tablespoons mix in cup and add 1 cup boiling water. Stir and enjoy.
Makes 50 servings.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Saute sliced mushrooms in butter.
Fry bacon until crisp, remove from pan and set aside.
In bacon drippings, brown beef cubes well (almost burnt).
Blend in flour.
Add sugar, salt, thyme, bay leaf, peppercorns, stock, and wine.
(If you don't like wine, substitute more stock.)
Cook for 1 hour.
Add onions.
Cook 1 hour more, adding wine or stock as needed and checking salt and pepper.

title: chicken with sundried tomatoes and pasta
directions: Cook the bow tie pasta and set aside.
Mince the garlic and saute in the olive oil.
Cut the chicken breasts into chunks and add to the sauteed garlic.
Cook until the chicken is white and push to the side of the pan.
Add the broccoli and cook for a couple of minutes.
Add the sundried tomatoes, seasonings, wine, chicken broth and butter.
Simmer for about five minutes.
Mix this with the cooked pasta and toss with some grated cheese to taste. Serve warm.

title: rotel
directions: Melt together. Serve warm with nachos or veggies.
(Can freeze.)

title: carrousel salad bowl
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
While still hot, drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Add onion, salt, pepper and cheese.
Toss well.
Gently mix in peas, ham, celery and mayonnaise.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on salad greens.

title: snow cream
directions: Puncture the eyes and drain off liquid.
Bake in a 350° oven for about an hour.
Hit the coconut with a hammer, and it will split right open.

title: sandy's shrimp creole
directions: Peel, devein and wash shrimp.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute until soft; stir in garlic.
Remove from heat; blend in flour until smooth. Add tomato sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
Gradually add water, stirring to blend.
Add shrimp and all remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer about 40 minutes.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: apple salad
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together apples, celery, nuts and grapes.
Coat with mayonnaise.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set pineapple aside.

title: waffles
directions: Place egg whites in small bowl and beat at speed 2 for two minutes or until moist peak forms.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into large bowl then add the egg yolks, milk and shortening or veg. oil.
Mix at speed 1 for one minute.
Add the beaten egg whites and mix at speed 1 for one-half minute.
Bake on hot waffle iron until golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger and sausage together.
Mix this mixture with the bread crumbs.
Mix eggs, milk, half of the ketchup, pepper, salt, celery seed, garlic salt, bell pepper and onion all together.
Mix the 2 mixtures together.
Add the milk to the meat mixture; mix well.
Cook for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy. Add oil, sugar, zucchini and pineapple; mix lightly, but well. Add flour, salt and baking powder. Mix until blended. Add nuts and raisins. Pour into greased bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: mexican tamales
directions: In serving dish (9 x 13-inch), place tamales (with wax paper wrappers removed), kidney beans, chili and black olives.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
During the last 15 minutes, put Doritos, slightly crushed, and Cheddar cheese on top of casserole.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add ground cranberries and orange.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet n' sour chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover with foil, then add pineapple rings and green pepper rings and bake 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: mary's best pecan pie
directions: Make
9-inch
pie crust and chill.
Mix all ingredients together.
Beat
on
Number 4 speed until well blended, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour
into chilled pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10
to 15 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Peel apples; cut in 1/8-inch slices.
Arrange on crust.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Sift 1/2 cup sugar with flour; cut butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hot cheese squares
directions: Grease a 12 inch x 15 inch pan.
Mix cheese and spread 1/2 mixture into pan.
Spread chopped pepper over first layer of cheese.
Spread remaining cheese on top.
Mix beaten eggs with milk and pour over second layer of cheese.	Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into 1 inch squares.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage, onion and peppers; strain grease and add rice. Simmer on low heat.

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, cream sugars, shortening, egg and vanilla.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add sugar to mixture and blend thoroughly.
Stir in optional ingredients.
On greased cookie sheet, drop a teaspoon of dough at a time.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until cookies are set but not hard.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: yum yum relish
directions: Chop the cabbage, tomatoes, onions, peppers and salt down overnight.
(Cover with water and 1 cup salt.)
Drain next morning and pour boiling water over to cover.
Drain well.
Mix vinegar, brown sugar, mustard, mustard seed, ginger, cinnamon and turmeric. Mix well and add vegetables.
Boil until thickened, about 45 to 50 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: chicken stock
directions: Remove skin and cut chicken into pieces.
In deep pot, cover chicken with water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Strain, reserving chicken and vegetables.
May be frozen.
Serving size 1 cup.

title: herbed beef kabobs
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling point and cool. Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes and add to the mixture in a Ziploc bag along with pepper squares, mushrooms and quartered onions.
Mix well. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: hamburger bean and bun casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix ground beef, beans, brown sugar and sauce.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in half and set cut side down around edge of casserole.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Arrange boneless chicken in 11 x 7-inch baking dish and place a piece
of
cheese
over
each.
Stir together soup and wine. Pour over chicken and cheese; sprinkle with stuffing on top and drizzle
melted
butter over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to
45 minutes until chicken is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen raspberry mousse
directions: Whip all ingredients in blender.
Freeze overnight in ring mold.
Unmold on round plate.
Garnish with leaves and serve drenched with Chambord (raspberry liqueur), if desired.
Serves 6.

title: easy pesto sauce
directions: Put basil and parsley in blender.
Blend with 1/4 cup olive oil at low speed.
Add cheese and remaining oil and blend.
Add nuts, blending until chopped.
Use over spaghetti or in soups or vegetables.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt in a 4-quart pan.
Bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda (this will swell).
Pour on the popcorn; stir. Place in 225° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool. Store in covered container to keep crisp.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave cheese out to soften.
Dice chipped beef and mix with parsley flakes, then divide in half.
Add rest of ingredients to 1/2 of the beef mixture.
Mix well and form into a ball. Refrigerate to make manageable.
Then roll ball into other half of beef mixture.
Refrigerate.
If you want to make a spread, just add all ingredients together.

title: pineapple-pecan pie
directions: Mix together pineapple, milk, pecans and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Divide between two crusts.
Refrigerate before serving.
Simple and delicious!!!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool 4 hours or more.

title: caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet.
Add brown sugar and stir until golden brown.
Beat together egg yolks and cornstarch; add to milk.
Add milk mixture to skillet and stir until thickened. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake in 450° oven until meringue is brown.

title: fluffy french toast
directions: Beat flour, sugar, salt, milk and eggs until smooth.
Soak bread in batter until saturated.
Cook in butter 12 minutes on each side or until golden brown.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Add chicken, corn, broth and salsa.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Sprinkle with cheese and let stand for 2 minutes.
Put in flat dish to melt cheese in 350° oven.

title: eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Dip each slice into egg then into crumbs and saute on both sides.
Put half the slices into casserole dish.
Top with half the cheese.
Add remaining eggplant.
Mix spaghetti sauce and water.
Pour over eggplant.
Add remaining slices over top; cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef and cabbage taco casserole - fantastic!!
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and set aside.
In the same beef skillet, stir-fry the shredded cabbage over high heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in ground beef.
Add green chili peppers, taco sauce, pepper and onion salt.
Mix well.
Mound into partially baked potato crust and bake for 20 minutes.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake for 2 to 3 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serve with taco sauce.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter or margarine, sugar, and vanilla for 3-4 minutes.
Stir in flour and pecans just until blended.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 20 minutes or until lightly brown around edges.
Let cool and sprinkle on powdered sugar.

title: crunchy almond chicken
directions: Place almonds, garlic and ginger root in a blender container. Cover and blend until finely ground.
Mix almond mixture, salt, paprika, cumin and pepper.
Dip chicken into margarine, then roll in almond mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up, in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Cook, uncovered, in 375° oven until thickest pieces are done, 55 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water and sugar.
Add lemonade, pineapple and strawberries.
Mix well.
When ready to serve, pour over ice in punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: fudge
directions: Scald milk; add chocolate until melted.
Put in sugar and syrup.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir.
Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir until dull sheen.
Pour in pan.

title: pineapple cake
directions: While cake is still hot, poke holes down in cake with wooden spoon.
Drain pineapple and spread on top of cake.
Cook pudding; pour over cake.
It will be runny.
When cake
and toppings cool, spread Cool Whip on top.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Brown ground meat and onions. Add mushroom slices, tomato sauce, tomato paste and 1 cup water. Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking. Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: quick and creamy salad
directions: Pour powdered jello over cottage cheese and mix.
Drain oranges and pineapple; stir in.
Add Cool Whip and stir.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Mix peanuts into melted chocolate chips and drop with a spoon on waxed-lined cookie sheets.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cheese) and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand 10 minutes, tossing with fork 2 to 3 times.
Place a layer of cooked mixture in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: lite fruit salad
directions: Reserve all juice but orange juice and mix it with pudding, then mix with other ingredients and chill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil 2 cups diced zucchini for 5 minutes in salt water, drain well.
Add all the above ingredients; mix together in a casserole dish.
Mix well.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour in greased dish (Corelle, Pyrex).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water and cool.
When Jell-O is cool, add fruit and let set up.

title: chocolate swirl cheese cake
directions: Crust:
In cereal bowl, use fork to cut butter into crackers. Stir in 2 teaspoons sugar.
Transfer mixture to 16 ounce casserole.
Press mixture against bottom and 1 1/2-inches up the side to form crust.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix Ricotta and cottage cheese with parsley and garlic.
Pour 1 cup of sauce into bottom of pan.
Arrange 1/3 of noodles in pan, touching, but not overlapping.
Spread 1/2 of cheese mixture over noodles; top with 1/2 of Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, starting again with sauce.
Top final layer should be noodles.
Cover with remaining sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 hour.

title: kathy's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Bake in greased tube pan in a 300° oven for
1 hour and 20 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in pan.
Boil until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from fire and when it begins to cool, add salt, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until it is creamy and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: icebox fruitcake(uncooked)
directions: Melt butter or margarine and marshmallows.
Mix all other ingredients in a very large bowl.
Pour melted mixture over these other ingredients.
Mix well; will have to use hands.
Divide into 3 portions and shape each portion into a round log.
Wrap in waxed paper and store in the refrigerator in Pringle potato chip cans.
(You do not need to chop the fruit and nuts because when you slice it, they will be chopped!)

title: diabetic spice cookie
directions: Boil water, shortening, raisins, dates, nutmeg and cinnamon for 3 minutes. Let cool. Then beat in eggs; dissolve salt, soda and sweetener in the 2 tablespoons of water. Then add egg mixture. Drop by teaspoon on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Fry hamburger, peppers and onion until veggies are tender; add tomato, zucchini and the spaghetti into large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; add cheese on top.

title: mexican fiesta casserole
directions: Grease a 10 x 14-inch casserole dish.
Line bottom with 6 tortillas.
Brown beef with chopped onion and garlic; season with chili powder, pepper and salt.
Mix beans and 1/2 cup water; stir into meat mixture.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over tortillas.
Cover with grated cheese.
Add 6 more tortillas and the rest of the meat.
Mix tomatoes and soup with 1/2 can water; spread over casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes after removing from the oven.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Slice yellow cake up and put in a punch bowl.
Pour a can of crushed pineapple over cake.
Add pudding.
Next, add cherry pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip and grated Hershey chocolate bar.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: houligan pancakes
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Mix flour, milk and eggs; pour over melted butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.
Serve with syrup or fruit.
Can be increased many times.
Recipe calls for salt; don't add salt.

title: honey scones
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until fine crumbs form.
With fork, blend milk, 2 tablespoons honey and egg. Turn all at once into flour.
Turn out on floured board and knead a few strokes until dough holds together.

title: polvorones
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Add vanilla and almond extract. Mix in sugar, flour and pecans.
Chill mixture for 1 hour.
Roll into 1 inch balls and then roll out into crescents.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
They should brown only slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet after cooling and roll in powdered sugar.

title: homemade silly putty
directions: Mix glue and starch well.
Let the mixture dry a bit to make it workable.
It may be necessary to add a little more glue or starch. This may not work well on a humid day.
Store in an airtight container.
Avoid contact with good clothing or carpet.

title: rice krispies sweets
directions: Cook brown sugar, egg, dates or raisins and salt in frying pan for 6 minutes.
Keep stirring.
When cool, add 2 cups of Rice Krispies.
Form into balls; roll in chopped nuts.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cheese.
Add eggs, well beaten. Alternate mixing into mixture the milk and flour.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Pour into cake baking pan (greased and floured).
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: You need an aluminum saucepan.

title: golden mediterranean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Add salad dressing and toss.
tags: Italian or Golden Mediterranean salad dressing

title: rock candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and water and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add 2 to 3 teaspoons of cinnamon oil and red food coloring.
Pour on aluminum foil-lined cookie sheet and allow to harden.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and break into pieces.

title: barbecued crock-pot chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together well; place in crock-pot.
Place fryer parts in crock-pot and stir into sauce well.
Cook on low overnight.
Chicken will be tasty and tender.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms well in cold water.
Drain.
Put in tightly covered container.
Add the dressing and shake well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Every once in a while, shake the container to mix. Good and easy.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions and garlic until vegetables are tender. Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 10 minutes. Stir occasionally. In a 2-quart casserole, layer 1/2 meat, 1 cup cheese and 1 cup chips.
Top with last 1/2 meat and chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: orange roughy
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Dip fillets.
Place in single layer, skin side down, on well-greased shallow pan. Combine potato chips and cheese.
Sprinkle on fillets.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: crab stew
directions: Add 1 cup flour in enough oil to brown for roux.
Brown to a very dark color.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper, garlic, tomato paste and season to taste.
Add water while cooking (enough to make a gravy, about medium).
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add crab bodies and simmer another 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Combine the margarine, brown sugar, flour and nuts with a pastry blender.
Remove one cupful to use for topping.
Press remainder into buttered 8 x 8 pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
To make filling, beat the cream cheese, sugar, egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla until smooth.
Turn onto baked crust.
Top with crumb topping.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: fruit party pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice cookie dough about 1/4-inch thick.
Place in circles in 10-inch pizza pan. Overlap slices slightly.
Press dough together with fingers to form crust.
Bake 10 minutes. Remove from oven, but leave oven on.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese 'n spinach casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions for 3 minutes.
Drain. Meanwhile, in large bowl, combine cheeses, spinach and eggs. Combine cooked noodles with 2 1/2 cups sauce; place half in a 3-quart casserole.
Top noodle mixture with cheese mixture, then remaining noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix taco dip and cream cheese with mixer in lg. bowl.
Spread into a cake pan.
Top with grated lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, and (olives).
Serve with Tortilla chips.

title: rice and spinach
directions: Saute
onions
in olive oil or butter; add spinach that has been
cooked
until wilted, rice, pepper, salt, dill weed and water.
Simmer for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: chicken in a crock-pot
directions: Put carrots and onions in bottom of crock-pot.
Add whole chicken.
Top with salt and pepper and liquid.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or on high for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours, using 1 cup of water.

title: bacon coleslaw
directions: Mix dressing and sugar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add enough flour to coat ground beef. You may add small amount of butter, if needed. Mix well. Add peas. Slowly add enough milk to make gravy. I put this on toast.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Combine crumbs, milk and beef. Shape into patties. Brown in fat.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over patties.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Garnish with onion rings.
Skillet or electric frypan works great!

title: shrimp-crab casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients top with cracker crumbs and bake 30 minutes at 350.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream potatoes, eggs, sugar and condensed milk together well. Fold in nuts, coconut, raisins and corn flakes.
Garnish with coconut; bake at 400°
for 40 minutes or according to the thickness of casserole.

title: date-nut-bumps
directions: Mix up ingredients for dough first, then mix in dates and nuts.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto baking sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil 3 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and beat until ready to spread.
You may add 1 teaspoon of vanilla or butter flavoring.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape dough into small mounds.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans; set aside.
Combine flour and the next 5 ingredients; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat sugar and oil.
Add eggs, water and pumpkin; beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients; stir just until blended.
Stir in nuts and raisins (optional).
Pour batter into greased loaf pans.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven to wire rack.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Let cool completely on wire racks.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 6 pieces.
Combine the sugar, cinnamon and pecans or raisins; shake in a bag.
Put 1/2 of the biscuits in a Bundt pan; sprinkle with 1/2 of the sugar and cinnamon.
Do the same with the rest of the biscuits, using all the sugar and cinnamon.
Boil the butter and brown sugar for 1 minute; pour over cake.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pig in the blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
First you get the rolling pin and the dough, then you flatten the dough. Next you get the cheese; place on the dough. Place the wiener on the cheese.
Roll the dough up. Cook the Pigs In The Blankets until golden brown.
Remove from oven and butter.

title: grits-sausage casserole
directions: Bring salted water to a boil.
Stir in grits.
Reduce heat and cook for 4 minutes.
Add cheese to grits, stirring until cheese is melted.
Combine eggs, milk, thyme and garlic.
Add some of the hot grits to egg mixture, stirring to blend.
Stir egg mixture into remaining grits.
Add cooked sausage.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 12-inch dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook at 350° for one hour.

title: tuna ball
directions: Form all ingredients into a ball and
roll in chopped pecans. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: nancy's nachos
directions: Fry ground beef until browned; drain excess fat.
Add chili seasoning and water according to package directions.
Saute for approximately 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and cook until meat looks "saucy".
Set aside.

Line a plate with chips, layer with meat, onions, green peppers, lettuce, tomatoes and picante sauce. Top with cheese, jalapeno peppers, black olives and sour cream. (Prepare enough chopped vegetables for 6 plates.)

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in enough water to barely cover with bouillon cube.
Cook until almost done.
Add sour cream, onions, bacon and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
I prefer to add the onions and bacon after I've put the soup in mugs.

title: calypso pie
directions: Mix cookies with melted butter and put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix coffee with boiling water and stir into ice cream. Spread over cookies and refreeze.

title: navajo tacos
directions: Mix together.
Try to mix in one direction like folding in. Raise in warm place for half an hour.
Pinch off pieces of dough about the size of an egg.
Pat and stretch into a circle about 8 inches across.
Fry in about an inch of hot shortening in a frypan.
Turn and brown the second side.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: sweet potato and apricot
directions: Place
cooked
sweet potato halves into buttered baking dish. Combine
brown
sugar,
cornstarch,
cinnamon, salt and orange peel in saucepan.
Drain apricot juice into cornstarch mixture. Cook
and stir over medium heat until boiling.
Boil 2
minutes. Add
apricots, butter and pecans; pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: cool mint pie
directions: Bake pie shell according to directions on package.
Melt chocolate bars and spread into bottom of baked pie crust.
Mix cream cheese, white chocolate pudding, and milk together in mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Then add
mint flavor, and food color until desired color.
Pour over chocolate in pie shell.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix well the pretzels, sugar and melted butter.
Place in a large Pyrex dish and bake for 6 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar and spread on pretzel mixture. Mix jello with boiling water and let dissolve.
Add strawberries. Let set until soft jell, then pour on top of creamed mixture. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small bite size pieces.
Place in any container.
Layer the rest of ingredients.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Pour into water.
Slowly bring to a boil. Pour over apples. Put in jars.
Pressure at 5 pounds pressure 3 minutes or according to apple toughness.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 2 cookie sheets with parchment paper.

title: chow mein
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots in butter.
Simmer.
Add other ingredients.
Cut chicken into approximately 1-inch cubes and brown in butter or peanut oil.
After all is cooked, may want to thicken with cornstarch.
I use my wok for this dish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and reserve liquid from oranges and pineapple.
Mix all fruits and pecans in a large bowl and toss, in separate bowl combine pudding mix and Tang with reserved fruit juices.
Whip to make a thick sauce.
Pour over fruit and allow to set overnight. (Whole frozen strawberries can be used but wait until just before serving to add them.)

title: christmas sparkle punch
directions: In bowl, press strawberries through a sieve.
Stir lime or lemon juice into pulp.
Cover and chill.
Place strawberry pulp into a large punch bowl.
Carefully pour pop and grape juice over pulp, stirring with an up and down motion.
When serving, garnish with lemon or lime slices.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix jello by directions on box.
Place in refrigerator and let thicken, but not gel.
Mix strawberries, sugar, salt and pecans together by hand.
Place in refrigerator and let chill.
Tear cake into small pieces.
When gelatin is thick, mix in half of the Cool Whip.
Add strawberry mixture and mix well.
Place a layer of cake in large serving bowl.
Spoon a layer of gelatin mixture, alternate, ending with jello on top.
Spread the remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: french onion soup
directions: Combine ingredients in large saucepan.
Simmer until onions are cooked.
Serve with garlic bread, apple slices and cheese cubes on the side.
Makes 7 (8 ounce) servings.

title: salsa
directions: Put tomatoes, peppers, onions and garlic in food processor. (Remove skins from tomatoes; also remove seeds from peppers for milder salsa.)
Add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in jars.
Heat lids before putting on jars.

title: vegetarian delight
directions: In small bowl, mix the peanut butter, soy sauce, 1 tablespoon water and honey; blend and set aside.
In large skillet or wok, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add carrots and onion; stir until onion is translucent, 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 3 minutes. Add peanut butter mixture; cook until boiling, 2 minutes.
Stir in rice; cook until heated through.
Arrange cashews on top.

title: vegetable yummies
directions: Cut washed celery into 3 or 4-inch lengths.
Fill ridges with choice of spreads above.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix according to directions on box.
Bake in greased pizza pan at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit over that. Mix 2/3 cup sugar, cornstarch, orange juice and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Reduce heat and continue cooking for 5 minutes and pour over fruit.
Refrigerate.
You can also use grapes, cut and drained, pineapple or blueberries!

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan (except chicken) and heat just to boiling.
Pour over cut up fryer in flat baking dish.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken breast with mallet until 1/8 inch thick.
Salt, pepper and parsley to taste.
On each breast, place one slice of cheese and one slice of ham (or bacon).
Roll up jelly roll fashion and secure with toothpick.
Brown chicken roll ups in oil or butter until golden brown.
Thin condensed soup with milk and pour over breast.
Bring to boil over medium heat, then simmer covered for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cushaw
directions: Wash cushaw well; remove seeds; cut into quarters.
Put cushaw in a kettle, filling half full with water.
Add sugar on top of cushaw.
Cook down until it becomes brown on the bottom.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice about 2 quarts cucumbers in bowl.
Salt very heavily and let stand for 4 hours.
Rinse in clear water, then pour boiling water to cover.
Let stand until cool enough to stand your hand in water.
Drain until dry.
Mix equal cups of sugar and vinegar; for instance, 1 cup sugar for 1 cup vinegar.
For one quart, use 1 tablespoon pickling spice.
For 1 pint, use 1 teaspoon.
Soaking cucumbers in a salt brine makes them crisp.
Use 1 cup salt to 2 quarts water.

title: southern chicken gumbo
directions: Saute onion in butter.
In large heavy pot, add all ingredients, except rice.
Bring to boil, stir in rice, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: gold cake
directions: Cream the butter and add the sugar gradually.
Beat the eggs until thick and add to the butter mixture.
Sift all dry ingredients and add alternately with the milk and vanilla.
Bake in three 7-inch square layer pans.
Moderate oven to 360° about 30 minutes.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Brown sausage slowly in a large skillet, pouring off the grease as it accumulates. Bring 4 1/2 cups water to a boil. Add rice and soup mix. Boil 9 minutes. Remove from heat, but do not drain. Mix browned sausage, rice mixture, green pepper, onion and celery. Put into a large greased casserole and sprinkle paprika, parsley and slivered almonds over the top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 12.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk, margarine and brown sugar.
Bring to a rolling boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Blend well and quickly until smooth with wooden spoon.
This will be thick.
Pat down smoothly into buttered oblong glass dish.
Sets up immediately as it cools. Recipe can be doubled.

title: opal's chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter. In separate pan, mix sugar, flour and cocoa. Pour into butter. Stir well. Add eggs one at a time. Stir well after each one. Add milk and vanilla. Pour into deep-dish unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rosy spring salad
directions: Combine rhubarb, water and sugar in a saucepan.
Cook until tender.
Pour this over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved. Add orange juice and rind.
Chill until syrupy.
Add strawberries.
Pour into an oiled container (6-cup mold). Chill until set. Makes 8 servings.

title: wild rice patties
directions: Make rice as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients and fry in large frying pan.
Serve plain or smothered in favorite sauce.

title: cranberry smoothie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sour cream and cranberry sauce.
Blend well.
Pour in mold.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix 1 cup Coca-Cola, margarine, cocoa and salad oil in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reserve remaining Coca-Cola for icing. Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Sift flour and sugar together.
Pour cocoa mixture over flour mixture.
Blend in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla well.
Do not use a mixer.
Pour into a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Yield: 24 servings.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 12 hours, or on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook noodles, drain.
Add tomato soup, ground beef and noodles together in a casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and vanilla. Stir in powdered sugar, cocoa and salt. Add milk, stirring until you reach desired spreading consistency. Use on favorite cake.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook Ro-Tel and cream of mushroom soup together.
Layer bottom of casserole dish with Doritos.
Pour chicken, Ro-Tel and soup in dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: mountain mama mud slide cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine butter, flour and pecans; mix well. Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°; cool.
In medium bowl, mix cream cheese and sugar until fluffy, then fold in 1 cup whipped cream.
spread over baked crust.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning and stir well.
Layer 1/2 of the chips in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer next ingredients in order:
hamburger meat, beans, soup, tomatoes, chips and cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: chicken-cabbage stir-fry
directions: Marinate chicken in teriyaki sauce 30 minutes at room temperature.
In wok, combine sherry, vinegar, 1 tablespoon oil and ginger root.
Add cabbage and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cook, covered, for 4 minutes.
Add broccoli and apples.
Cook, covered, 3 minutes more.
Remove cabbage.
Discard liquid in wok. Drain chicken.
Heat remaining oil and stir-fry chicken 3 to 4 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: hawaiian chicken wings
directions: Mix the last 9 ingredients together; stir until there are no lumps in the batter.
Put thawed wings in batter and marinate overnight.
Stir several times.
Before deep frying, stir again, then fry until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: french onion soup with garlic toast
directions: Cut onions in half and cut into thin slices.
Brown in Dutch oven with olive oil.
Fill pot with onions and water.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add bouillon cubes, if desired.

title: tree soup - lo-cal low cholesterol
directions: Mix all together in large pot.
Cook until tender.

title: praline bars
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with graham crackers.
In a saucepan, put sugar and butter or margarine.
Bring to a boil and boil only 2 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour over crackers and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with chips, crackers or bread cubes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine butter, sugar and peanut butter and roll into balls. Dip in melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix together meat, soup, milk, chopped onion and cheese. Layer in casserole with cooked macaroni.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chuck's chile con carne
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in 3-quart saucepan, stirring occasionally, until beef is brown; drain. Stir in remaining ingredients except beans.
Break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 415 calories per serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put sugar and cornstarch mixture in jello.
Cook until thick. Let cool.
Add 1 cup strawberries.
Put into graham cracker crust. Let chill.
Then put Cool Whip and 1 cup strawberries on top.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on box, omitting seasoning. Drain. Add 1 stick margarine and cut up cheese. Stir and pour in casserole dish. Crush crackers. Add softened margarine and put on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat
egg whites until stiff;
add 1/2 cup sugar gradually while continuing to beat.
Roll or blend crackers to very fine crumbs
and
mix in along with 1/2 cup sugar and fold in nuts. Fold
this into egg mixture and add vanilla.
Pour into well-greased
pie
plate
(9-inch) and bake 30 minutes in 325° oven.
When done, set for 4 hours, then top with whipped cream with pineapple mixed in.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: make ahead lasagna
directions: Place 1 cup of spaghetti sauce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer noodles, ground beef, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and remaining spaghetti sauce (ending with spaghetti sauce).
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Pour water around edges.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Remove foil and bake 15 more minutes, uncovered.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
May be made ahead and refrigerated overnight before baking.

title: hot sausage bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease baking sheets.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Shape into small balls and place on baking sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve while hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: 14 carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add sugar, oil and eggs and mix well.
Add carrots, drained pineapple, coconut and nuts.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix and put into boiler.
Stir while cooking on low heat. Flavor with lemon rind and juice or lemon flavoring.
Bring to a boil on low heat.
Serve warm on plain vanilla or lemon cake.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells and let cool.
Cook hamburger and onion over low heat until meat is brown.
Drain.
Pour sauce over mixture and simmer for 10 minutes.
Grate cheeses.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, spread 1 cup of sauce.
Stuff shells with the cheeses.
Arrange in single layer in pan.
Spoon remaining sauce over shells.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake with foil covering for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Serves 6 people.

title: benne wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place the benne (sesame) seeds on an ungreased baking sheet and toast for 10 to 12 minutes, until light brown.
Watch close so that they don't burn.

In a large bowl mix the brown sugar, melted butter or margarine, egg, vanilla extract, flour, salt, baking powder and toasted sesame seeds together until combined. Drop dough by 1/2 teaspoonfuls 1 1/2 inches apart onto a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 4 to 6 minutes, until light brown.
