Let cookies cool for about 2 minutes before removing from baking sheets to a wire rack to cool completely. Store cooled cookies in an airtight container.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook noodles as box directions suggest.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Mix all remaining ingredients and place in large baking dish.
Cook for 20 minutes at 375°.
Add cheese and melt.

title: russian tea
directions: Heat allspice in water.
Strain.
Squeeze lemons and add with spices to tea.
Strain and strain again for clearness.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter, salt and grated chocolate.
Cover until boiling point is reached.
Boil to a soft ball stage.
Add flavoring and cool.
Beat until mixture is creamy thick.
Pour into well buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: mound candy
directions: Melt Eagle Brand milk and oleo in double boiler.
Pour over next mixture of powdered sugar, coconut and nuts.
Put in greased pan and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Take out and cut into small pieces; dip in next mixture of chocolate chips and paraffin and put on wax paper.
Makes about 70 pieces.

title: pecan pie
directions: In
a large bowl, stir eggs, syrup, sugar, oleo and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: sweet-and-sour chinese meatballs
directions: Blend together ground beef, salt, pepper and ginger.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Heat oil in wok or skillet; brown meatballs on all sides, about 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve at once with rice. Yields 4 servings.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and pour the pumpkin mixture in.
Mix together only until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into 2 or 3 medium size loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: white chocolate cheesecake pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with 1/2 cup of milk.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk.
Add pudding and Cool Whip.
Beat well.
Makes 2 pies.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Scald the milk.
Add the shortening and sugar.
Stir until dissolved, then add the cold water.
Crumble in the yeast, stirring until dissolved.
Add the egg and flour; knead to get rid of stickiness.
Roll into rectangle.
Add filling.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until done. Put in baking dish and mix in all other ingredients. Top with 1 cup cornflakes and 1/2 cup melted butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° about 15 minutes.
Will not turn golden brown.
Do not overbake.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in the 1/4 cup warm water.
Heat 1 cup water, honey and butter until it is warm.
Pour into the dissolved yeast in bowl.
Add salt and egg; mix well.
Add flour and work into a dough.
Let rise until doubled, form into a loaf, put in bread pan and let rise again.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes, putting foil over it for last 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a 2-1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Will turn golden brown on top.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove 1/2 cup dry cake mix; reserve.
Beat remaining dry cake mix, butter, eggs and sour cream in large bowl on medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spread half of the batter in pan.
Stir together reserved dry cake mix, brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter in pan.
Carefully spread remaining batter evenly over pecan mixture.
(To make spreading easier, drop batter by dollops over pecan mixture, then spread.)
Bake 30 to 33 minutes or until deep golden brown and cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Stir powdered sugar, milk and vanilla until thin enough to drizzle, stirring in additional milk, 1 teaspoon at a time, if necessary.
Poke top of warm cake several times with fork; spread glaze over top of cake. Cool completely, about 1 hour.
Store covered.

title: seafood cocktail dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill two hours.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups of dip.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cover bottom of skillet with cooking oil. Make a roux by adding flour and browning. Saute onion and bell pepper in roux.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into prepared graham cracker pie crust.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: lemon cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat 5 minutes.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix a small amount of sugar at a time using drops of cream as needed to moisten. Add butter and vanilla. Shape into balls around cherries and dip into melted mixture of chocolate chips and paraffin. Let cool and enjoy.

title: treet salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Onions can be added.
May be used as sandwich spread or served on lettuce with crackers.

title: butterscotch pudding cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and set aside.

Combine the remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat 2 minutes. Pour 1/3 batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, then 1/3 brown sugar mix, then another layer of first mixture, etc., ending with last of brown sugar and nut mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: potato candy
directions: Put hot potatoes through ricer to remove lumps, then beat in butter.
Put potatoes in mixing bowl and beat in sugar.
Add cocoa and beat throughly.
Mix in vanilla, salt and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator to harden candy.
Keep in tightly closed container.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In a 9x13 inch dish, place a layer of sliced potatoes. Then add a layer of sliced onions. Make as many layers as you wish. Lay pork chops on top of potatoes and onions. Spread can of cream of chicken soup, no water added, on top of the pork chops. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: cheese danish
directions: Combine cheese, egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla in bowl. Mix with electric mixer on high until creamy, about 3 minutes. Set aside.
Unroll 1 package dough, evening in 13 x 9-inch pan, pressing down to close perforations.
Spread cheese mixture evenly on dough.
Unroll other package dough evenly over filling.
Whip egg whites with fork in small bowl until frothy; spread evenly atop dough.
Sprinkle with remaining 3/4 cup sugar, cinnamon for color and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Allow to cool and set; then slice into bars.
Makes 16 to 24 bars.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together the Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt. Make a hole; add the buttermilk, oil and eggs.
Mix with spoon. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put in container and keep in refrigerator.
Will keep 6 weeks.

title: fresh broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until tender; leave some water in the pan.
Add chicken broth.

title: peanut butter-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease cookie sheet.

title: cool whip jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple; add Jell-O and dissolve.
Add creamed cottage cheese.
When it jells, add the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: carrot fruitcake
directions: Combine nuts, fruit, dates and raisins with 1/2 cup flour. Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine sugar and oil.
Mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and remaining flour.
Gradually add to sugar mixture.
Spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan to cool on a wire rack.
If desired, drizzle with confectioners sugar icing when cooled.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: mexican slaw
directions: Shred all together. Add sugar and vinegar. Cover 20 days in refrigerator.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients with milk and water.
Add flavoring and beat well.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Start in cold oven at 325°.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: clare's strawberry delight
directions: Prepare Dream Whip with milk and vanilla according to package directions. Fold in orange peel and nuts, blending thoroughly.
On waxed paper lined baking sheet, spoon heaping tablespoonfuls of mixture to form 6 mounds.
Shape center of each mound into a shell with back of spoon.
Freeze until firm. Fill centers of each shell with strawberries.
Yields 6 servings.

title: quick stroganoff
directions: Cut meat across grain diagonally, 1/4-inch strips wide.
In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons margarine; add 1/2 of meat. Saute quickly both sides, stirring constantly.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Repeat with remaining meat and margarine.
Move to side of skillet.
Add onion.
Cook, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add drained mushrooms, water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil.
Combine sour cream, yogurt and flour in small bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Stir into skillet (using a whisk).
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: butterscotch clusters
directions: Melt together in heavy saucepan over low heat the butterscotch morsels and peanut butter.
Stir constantly until well blended. Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let stand in a cool place until firm.
Makes about 4 dozen confections, 1 1/2 inches in diameter.

title: potato cheese casserole(servings:  18)
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine.
Saute onion until clear. Add sour cream, soup and cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Gently fold in hash browns.
Pour all into large casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Stir together melted butter and cereal. Sprinkle over casserole and return to oven for an additional 5 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Bake in greased and floured tube cake pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meatballs in red wine sauce
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Dredge in flour.
Brown meatballs in batches in oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Remove from skillet; set aside.
Combine tomato sauce and remaining ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Add meatballs.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 35 minutes.
Yields 9 dozen.

title: spoon cake
directions: Make cake according to box.
Make 1 package pudding at a time, according to box.
In large serving bowl, crumble 1/2 cooked cake on bottom of bowl.
Top with 1/4 cup Kahlua.
Add 1 box pudding (mixed).
Add 1/2 Cool Whip.
Add 2 crumbled Skor bars.
Repeat layers.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Cut and mix into large bowl.
Let stand in refrigerator so sugar in coconut will soak in rest of fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Crust:
Spread crescent rolls flat on pizza pan.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes and let cool.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, egg and almond extract.
Blend ingredients well and add the dry ingredients a little at a time. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: banana nut spice cake
directions: Mash the bananas.
Pour vegetable oil over the bananas and let stand while mixing cake.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in banana mixture and mix well. Add dry ingredients which have been combined. Stir in raisins and pecans; mix thoroughly. Spoon into 3 greased loaf pans and bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grandma's ginger snaps
directions: *Cookies baked with butter will be soft and chewy; cookies baked with Crisco will be crunchier.

title: wilted leaf lettuce
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble, reserving drippings. Add onions to drippings and cook until tender. Add vinegar, 1/2 water, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and bacon. Cook and stir until boiling. Pour hot dressing over lettuce; toss to coat.

title: veggie people
directions: Wash and slice vegetables.
Arrange vegetable slices on a plate.
Mix one tablespoon of cream cheese and your favorite food color (just a few drops).
Using a toothpick, dot eyes on veggies (mouth and nose, too).
Dip veggies into Ranch dressing for a fun snack.
(Healthy too!)

title: danish apple squares
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add egg and milk mixture and blend.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll half of the dough to fit 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan or an oblong baking pan.
Sprinkle bottom of crust of dough with corn flakes.
Combine apples, sugar and cinnamon. Spread mixture over corn flakes and put on top.
Pinch together to seal edges.
Beat egg white stiff and brush over top crust.
Bake in 400° or 375° oven for 50 minutes or until golden.
Drizzle confectioners sugar over the cooked crust (1 cup confectioners sugar, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1 to 2 tablespoons water).

title: cherry dessert
directions: This lets you concentrate on the food, but is ready and perfect for after dinner!

title: frozen apples
directions: Mix and let stand overnight. Cook until nearly tender.
Cool and freeze. These apples are good for fried apple pies.

title: never fail drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Spoon cookie dough onto the pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Wrap Smokies with bacon.
Mix ketchup and sugar and pour over Smokies.
Place in a pie plate or small baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix soups; bring to a boil.
In a large baking dish, put a layer of beef, layer of potatoes and layer of onions until all used.
Pour soups over each layer.
Bake 1 hour in preheated 350° oven.

title: harvard beets
directions: Heat together beets and beet juice and water; mix together and stir in flour, sugar salt, pepper and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly until smoothly blended and thickened.

title: double quick baked beans
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a skillet.
Add onion and cook over medium heat until soft, stirring occasionally.
Blend in ketchup, molasses, Tabasco, brown sugar, salt and dry mustard. Bring to boiling.
Stir in baked beans.
Put mixture into casserole dish.
Put bacon across top of beans.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes or until bacon is cooked.

title: excellent cookies
directions: Sift into large bowl the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; add the rest of the ingredients.
Beat for 3 minutes on medium speed. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: quick fudge sauce
directions: Place chocolate chips in blender container.
In 1-quart saucepan, combine cream, water and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Add to chips.
Cover and blend until smooth, about 1 minute.

title: creamy timbale tacos
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add beans, chili and tomatoes.
Heat all together, then add the cheese (grated or cubed) and whipping cream.
Heat and serve over Doritos with your favorite taco topping or just serve as a dip.

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Dissolve brown sugar in water.
Pour juices and brown sugar mixture into automatic percolator.
Place cloves and cinnamon in percolator basket.
Allow to go through cycle.
Serve piping hot.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix everything but ginger ale and sherbet.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and sherbet.

title: cereal ice cream surprise
directions: You will need 1 coffee mug.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into strips 1/2-inch wide by 1 1/2-inches long. Dredge meat in mixture of flour, salt and pepper and brown in margarine.
Add chopped onions and brown.
Drain can sliced mushrooms.
Save mushroom liquid and add enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Set aside mushrooms until later.

title: horseshoes
directions: Knead the mixture made from the first 5 ingredients
until it does not stick on hands.
Put in Ziploc bag.
Put in pan of cold water until it floats.
Open bag; wrap in towel and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.
Grind walnuts.
Add sugar to your sweetness.
Melt the oleo.
Roll like pie dough on granulated sugar.
Cut into 2 x 4-inch shapes.
Put nuts on; roll and shape like horseshoes.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: quick and easy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°; lay legs or wings around pan (side by side).
Mix together seasonings and sprinkle all over chicken.
Chop or slice onion and toss all over chicken.
Mix together in separate bowl the soup and sherry, then put spoonfuls all over top of onion and chicken.
Put pats (tablespoons) of margarine or butter all across top of soup mixture.
Cover pan or baking dish with foil and bake.
Bake 1 hour or until chicken is very tender.
Yum, yum ...
"The sauce (after chicken is done) goes great with rice or mashed potatoes."
Enjoy.

title: freezer ice cream
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, using 3 cups milk.
Cook until thick.
Add sugar gradually; add vanilla and salt.
Add pudding mixture to beaten eggs, beating constantly. Pour into freezer container.
Add milk until 2/3 full.
Freeze.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef; mix well.
Add ground beef; mix lightly, but thoroughly. Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Add Jell-O, sugar and 1/4 cup water together.
Beat egg yolks, then the 3 cups of water, margarine and lemon juice.
Mix together well.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add meringue on top.
Bake at 360° until golden brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese until creamy.
Add vanilla and salt, then 1 egg at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour.
Pour
into
a
greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: peanutty chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream and eggs; mix together well. Place 12 scoops of batter into bottom of a fluted stoneware cake pan, rubbed with butter. Top with Reese's Cups. Place remaining batter on top. Microwave on High 11 to 14 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes; loosen from sides and invert on plate. Place peanut butter in microwave for 20 to 40 seconds or until melted. Drizzle over cake, allowing it to run down sides. Place morsels and oil in microwave for 20 to 30 seconds or until melted and drizzle over cake. Sprinkle chopped nuts over cake.

title: whip cream frosting
directions: Heat to dissolve gelatin.
Let cool.
Beat vanilla and cream until thick.
Add sugar, then gelatin mixture gradually.

title: champagne dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add drained pineapple, diced bananas, walnuts, strawberries and Cool Whip.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: baby food cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
Stir in other ingredients until well blended.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomato paste, mushrooms and season to taste.
Grease 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Line with biscuits.
Fill with meat mixture.
Top with tomato and pizza cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 slices.

title: chicken casserole oriental
directions: Drain mushrooms, reserve 3 tablespoons liquid.
Melt margarine in skillet; saute onion until tender.
Stir in green pepper, celery, chicken broth and soy sauce.
Add chicken and mushrooms. Mix cornstarch and liquid from mushrooms; stir into chicken mixture.
Add nuts, water chestnuts and rice.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes or until rice is soft.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Pepper and onion are optional.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in lemon peel, juice and margarine.
Combine yolks and milk.
Add to flour mixture; stir until all combined.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Gently fold egg whites into lemon batter.
Transfer batter to a 1-quart casserole dish.
Place on oven rack in a larger pan.
Add hot water to oven pan 1-inch deep.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm!
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo; mix with dressing.
Spread half of it in an 8-inch baking dish.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix
cups
of
flour with the other dry ingredients, including
yeast.
Put
the
Crisco
in the warm water and add this
mixture to the dry ingredients.
Beat at medium speed on the mixer for 2 minutes.
Add the remaining flour and mix with a wooden
spoon
until
thoroughly
blended.
Turn out onto a floured
surface
and knead until smooth.
Grease 2 large loaf pans and form dough into 2 loaves.
Brush the top of each loaf with
melted
butter.
Cover
and set in a warm place to rise. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Remove from pans and brush all over with melted butter.

title: kelly cheese squares
directions: Soften butter and cheese to room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients (except bread) and mix well.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat in a greased skillet.
Add onions, potatoes and seasonings and cook until vegetables are done.
If you do not have onions on hand, you may use Lipton's dry onion soup mix, will not take much or any seasoning.

title: special bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Line 12 muffin cups.
Fill about half full.
Bake at 350° until well done.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Take crescent rolls and form a crust in 8 x 10-inch pan. Brown sausage.
Layer sausage, potatoes and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over layers.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: leek soup
directions: Cut off roots and dark green leaves of leeks.
Chop white and pale green portions of leeks.
Saute leeks in Dutch oven until limp.
Add broth and potatoes.
Simmer approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken breast dinner
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add chicken and brown. Add soup, water and vegetables. Heat to a boil and cover. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: stuffed mushrooms with crab meat
directions: Dice crab meat so it is tiny pieces; put lemon juice over or squeeze fresh lemon on crab meat.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons of sour cream with crab meat and mix.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture; cover with Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 20 minutes or until mushrooms are soft and cheese is melted.

title: mexican chicken and spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Pour in Ro-Tel.
When mixture is hot, remove from stove.
Drain spaghetti.
Put melted Ro-Tel mixture and chicken in pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bay football bars
directions: Melt sugar and syrup until it bubbles (medium heat). Add peanut butter; mix. Add Rice Krispies; mix. Remove from heat and smooth into large cake pan.

title: outstanding oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy; blend in egg and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour, soda and salt and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool 3 minutes and remove from pan.
Yield:
4 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: salad dressing for potato or macaroni salad
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, pepper, vinegar, water and eggs in saucepan.
Cook and stir on medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Add mustard and mayonnaise to saucepan.
Mix well.
Pour over already prepared potato or macaroni salad.

title: weight watcher gazpacho cooler
directions: Pour vegetable juice into an ice cube tray, making 10 cubes. Freeze until solid.
Cut 2 slices from cucumber and reserve for garnish.
Pare and seed remaining cucumber, then cut into pieces. In blender, combine cucumber, pepper, onion, lime juice, vinegar, garlic and hot sauce.
Process on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in seltzer.

title: french pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and process at Mix until smooth.
Heat electric skillet.
Brush with butter and pour batter in four pancakes.
Flip when needed.
Serve with butter and syrup.
Could also be used as crepes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Cut cake in small pieces and place half in an oblong pan.
Melt chips and after cooling add eggs and vanilla.
Fold whipping cream into mixture.
Pour half of mixture over the cake pieces.
Put 1/2 of mixture over this.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Bake chicken at 350° until done.
Cut into narrow strips. Heat oil and briefly dip tortillas to soften; drain.
Layer all ingredients in a glass lasagne pan as follows:
5 tortillas, 1/4 of chicken, 1/4 of vegetables, 1/4 of Mexican tomatoes and 1/4 of each of the cheeses.
Repeat for 3 more layers; top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let rest for 10 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with fresh basil or cilantro leaves, if desired. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Blend chili, jelly and lemon juice.
Bring to boil.
Combine meat with finely chopped onion, pepper and ice water.
Roll into meatballs and drop into sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid. Fry salt pork until crisp in large saucepan.
Remove; add water, potatoes, onion and reserved clam liquid to fat in saucepan.
Cook, covered, until potatoes are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add milk, cream, clams and salt pork. Heat slowly, just to boiling.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Float butter atop each serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spiced apple corn fritters
directions: In a deep, heavy saucepan, heat 4 inches of vegetable oil to 350°.
In bowl with a heavy-duty mixer, beat together corn, egg, baking powder, salt and sugar on medium speed (can do by hand). Add 3 cups flour and mix on low speed until blended.
Sprinkle in enough remaining flour so that dough is thick and does not stick to side of bowl.
By hand, knead in flour until dough is no longer sticky.

title: salmon
directions: You will need pint jars, lids and rings.

title: kale soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large pot.
Add linguica and fry up, then add half pot of water.
Add potatoes; cook on high heat until boiling, then add beans, cabbage, kale, salt and pepper.
Add some ketchup for color.
Cook on medium heat until potatoes and soup are done, about 20 minutes, then turn to low and simmer.

title: mystery bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Spray with Pam or equivalent. Place crackers on pan in a single layer (like a checkerboard). Mix and boil butter and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until crackers float and/or mixture bubbles.
Take out of oven and immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Chips will melt and should be spread evenly over pan with back of a spoon.
Sprinkle pan with nuts.
Score individual crackers with knife.
Refrigerate and finish cutting when cold.
Keep bars refrigerated or in freezer.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine in large dish tuna, noodles and pickles, sliced up.
Add mayonnaise to taste.
Chill and serve.

title: bacon-cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix together all ingredients and spread on toast points. Broil 6 minutes at 2 inches from broiler.
Serve hot.

title: daffodil cake
directions: Beat 6 egg whites with 1 teaspoon cream of tartar until very stiff.
Mix all other ingredients together and add to egg whites. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes in an ungreased tube pan. Invert cake when done.

title: shake and bake mix
directions: Mix well. Dip chicken, etc. in milk or water. Shake in mixture and bake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and onion; cool.
Fold in soup, eggs and mayonnaise well.
Add cheese, broccoli and onion.
Grease glass baking dish with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: v-8 tomato cocktail
directions: Clean fish and sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
In the morning, rinse and pack in pint or quart jars.
Add 1/2 c. mazola oil to each pint.
Put on cover and process in pressure cooker for 90 minutes at 10 pounds of pressure.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Bring to boil in saucepan the margarine, cocoa and boiling water. Pour in sugar and flour mixture. Add buttermilk, beaten egg, soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Mix well. Pour in greased and floured 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet with 3/4-inch sides. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: meringue surprises
directions: Beat egg whites on high until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and beat until glossy.
May add 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes on cookie sheet before removing. Be careful not to burn.
No fat or cholesterol.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with eggs.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes in 3 (9-inch) round greased and floured pans.
Frost with a double batch of cream cheese frosting and decorate with pecan halves.

title: praline pie
directions: Take coconut, butter and pecans and place in iron skillet to brown.
Mix cream cheese with milk with mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip. Mix well.
Layer cream cheese mixture, coconut and pecans. Drizzle caramel topping.
Repeat.
Will make 3 small pies or 2 large pies.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients
and
work with hands.
Roll in balls; place on cookie sheet
with
wax
paper.
Chill
for
1 hour. Melt almond bark and
dip
chilled balls and place back on wax paper until hardened.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix corn flakes and melted butter and cover bottom of pan. Layer the next 4 ingredients.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the top.
Top with remaining buttered corn flakes.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mound bars
directions: Lightly grease 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Mix first 4 ingredients well and spread in pan evenly.
Freeze.
Cut in small squares.

title: quick and easy french dressing
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding, milk and Eagle Brand milk; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Layer Nilla wafers, bananas and pudding, repeating 3 times.

title: cocoa
directions: Place water and salt in a medium sized pan over low heat.
Add sugar and cocoa, stir to dissolve, and heat for 10 minutes.

title: cheese and bacon biscuits
directions: Mix sugar and flour well.
Mix buttermilk and soda together. Mix together all ingredients and make biscuits.

title: pumpkin and apple casserole
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter and combine with sugar, cinnamon, nuts and salt.

title: peanutty chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix in large bowl
at
medium speed peanut butter, corn syrup, oleo, eggs	and
vanilla
until
smooth.
Reduce speed; beat in flour, baking
powder and salt until blended.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate
chips.
Spread
evenly in ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan. Bake at
for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Melt rest of chocolate; drizzle over surface.
Cut into bars.
Makes 48.

title: herbed beef stew
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large kettle and brown well the beef chuck, cut into cubes.
Add mushrooms, onions, garlic, salt, dill, basil, thyme, savory, bay leaves and pepper.
Saute slowly, stirring occasionally until mushrooms and onions are tender.
Now add can of beef consomme and cans of tomatoes.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

Add 1 pound small white onions, peeled and 1 bunch carrots, peeled and cut into 2-inch chunks. Cover kettle and cook 45 minutes more or until vegetables are done. Now mix 6 tablespoons flour with 1/2 cup cold water until smooth and add gradually to the stew, stirring occasionally. Continue to stir and heat until gravy is thickened.

title: a round of spinach dip
directions: Mix thoroughly at least 2 hours before serving.

title: onion casserole
directions: Place a layer of onions in the bottom of a greased dish. Cover with a layer of almonds, then a layer of soup.
Repeat the 3 layers; cover with crushed corn flakes.
Pour melted butter over all.
Cook until golden and the onions are soft at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: sweet and sour cucumber salad(diabetic:  low-fat)
directions: Boil water, vinegar, sweetener, pickle and salt.
Place cucumbers and celery slices in a glass jar.
Pour boiling liquid over. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Drain before serving. Yields 2 cups.
Contains 20 calories per serving.

title: lemon rounds (cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg, lemon juice (rind of lemon, if desired).
Combine flour with baking powder, salt and crushed lemon drops.
Add to creamed mixture. Mix on high speed with mixer until well-blended.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes; remove from sheets and cool.
Frost if desired.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix just before serving.

title: bean and burger bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in pork and beans, ketchup, onion, mustard and salt; simmer, uncovered.

title: rhubarb rosy swirls
directions: Make a	syrup of sugar and water.
Cook to a thin syrup and add the
lemon
juice
and	butter.
Pour
this into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix
cups	of Bisquick as directed on box for biscuits. Roll
dough
into a rectangle about 1/4-inch thick. Arrange 3 cups finely cut rhubarb on dough and roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut into
9 to 12 pieces and place in the syrup. Sprinkle with	sugar and
bake
at
400° to 425° until nicely browned.
Serve with cream or ice cream.
Best served warm.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter and melted oleo in large bowl.
Add sugar and Rice Krispies.
Make balls and dip in melted chocolate.

title: the cake that won't last
directions: Add all ingredients.
Stir well, but do not beat.
Pour into Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: thai chicken with basil
directions: Cut each chicken breast half into 4 pieces. Heat oil in wok or 12 inch skillet over medium high heat. Cook garlic and chilies in oil, stirring constantly, until garlic is golden brown. Add chicken; stir-fry 8 to 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center. Stir in fish sauce and sugar. Sprinkle with basil and mint. This has 5 grams carbohydrates.

title: deviled ham and cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
To serve, place in bowl on tray along with choice of crackers, breads, carrot sticks or celery sticks.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Step 1:
Mix cornbread mix as directed on box.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening and butter.
Add brown and white sugars.
Blend.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat mixture until light; add nutmeats.
Blend in dry ingredients and mix well.
Divide dough in 2 parts and make 2 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper; chill overnight in refrigerator.
Slice off and bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice onions about 1/8-inch thick and separate into rings. Roll each ring in flour, then dip in mixture made of the eggs and milk.
Roll in cracker crumbs and fry in a wire basket in furiously boiling cooking oil.
Remove and drain.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Beat cherry pie mixture until cherries are in bits.
Add eggs and cake mix.
Beat until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Add all ingredients together in a jar.
Shake and add to salad.

title: praline biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place 2 teaspoons butter, 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 or 3 pecans in each of 12 greased medium muffin cups. Sprinkle cinnamon in each cup.
Stir baking mix and water to a soft dough.
Drop dough by spoonfuls into each cup.
Bake 15 minutes.
Invert onto tray.
Let pan remain over biscuits a few minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: good potato salad
directions: Mix all together and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: poppy seed noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Brown butter in skillet; add poppy seed and almonds, mixing well.
Add noodles and toss lightly to mix.

title: banana oat bread
directions: Combine oats, baking powder and salt in a bowl. Combine bananas, honey, oil and eggs in blender container. Process until smooth. Add to dry ingredients; mix well. Stir in pecans.
Spoon into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done. Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: tuna macaroni salad(makes 8 servings)
directions: Rinse cooked macaroni in cold water; drain well.
Combine all other ingredients except paprika.
Cover and chill.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese for large numbers(14 to 16 people)
directions: Thaw macaroni and cheese and mix in the remaining ingredients.

title: almond chicken(stir-fry)
directions: Skin, bone and cut up chicken breasts into 1/2-inch cubes. In a bowl, mix ginger, honey and cornstarch and blend in water, soy sauce and sherry.
Thaw pea pods.
In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add almonds, stirring and cooking for about 3 minutes.
Add chicken and cook just until meat turns white. Pour in sherry mixture and cook until sauce thickens.
Add pea pods and stir until hot and glazed.
Serve over rice.
(Cashews may be substituted for the almonds.)

title: swiss steak
directions: Rub steak with flour.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sear in frying pan in oil.
Remove and place in casserole dish.
In the same pan, saute onion and mushrooms.
Pour over steak.
Cover meat with 1 inch of water.
Bake in oven, covered, for 2 hours at 350°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato and pork chop casserole
directions: Spray large baking dish with Pam.
Layer sliced potatoes then pork chops then another layer of sliced potatoes and mushrooms. Season if you wish to.
Pour soup and liquid over this.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until tender.
Add cheese and crackers to top of casserole.
Bake in oven, uncovered, until cheese is melted and top is lightly browned.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole in even layer.
Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper; pour over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in 9 x 13 pan. Top with 1 cup of crushed corn flakes and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: garlic cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Chill at least 3 hours.
(Can serve at once.)
Stir before serving.

title: deviled puffs
directions: Prepare puffs and filling early in day.
Fill at party time.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Saute onion.
Drain half the liquid from the peas.
Mix peas, soup, pimento and water chestnuts.
Add onion.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Top with cheese; crumble crackers in melted margarine and spread on top of cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: eggnog cake
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Grease and flour two layer cake pans. Combine
flour,
sugar,
baking
powder,
salt, nutmeg, eggs, vanilla, eggnog
and
butter
into	a large mixing bowl. Blend well at medium
speed.
Pour into pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken with mushrooms
directions: Brown chicken breasts in skillet in 1/4 stick butter on both sides.
Remove from skillet and place in baking dish.
Add celery, mushrooms and mushroom soup.
Add soup can of water.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven until tender.
Continue to baste chicken so it will not dry out.

title: fresh orange waldorf salad
directions: Grate peel of 1/2 fresh orange.
Peel and cut oranges in bite-size pieces.
Cut apple (do not peel) in bite-size pieces. Combine all ingredients and chill well.
Serve on salad greens if desired.

title: cranberry candy
directions: In a 2 to 3-quart pan, combine cranberries, orange peel and orange juice. Set over medium-high heat and cook for about 15 minutes or until cranberries soften and pop open.
Cool.
Whirl mixture
a little at a time in a blender until smooth, then force through a fine wire strainer; discard residue.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Cream the shortening; add the sugar gradually and continue working until light and fluffy. Add the eggs and beat well. Add the flour mixture alternately with the bananas a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth. Pour into a well-greased bread pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inches) and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: magic tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, oil from tuna, cheese, seasonings and 1/4 cup bread crumbs into beaten eggs.
Turn into oiled 1-quart casserole and top with remaining crumbs.
Dot with butter.

title: herbed seafood and pasta
directions: Clean and devein shrimp/scallops.
Melt butter; add garlic and seafood.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from butter and set aside. Add half and half to butter in pan.
Bring to boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Add seafood, parsley and seasonings.
Heat well.
Serve over cooked pasta surrounded by pepper.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake a white or yellow cake; cool.
Mix vanilla pudding, milk and cream cheese with a mixer.
Spread pudding mixture on cooled cake.
Spread crushed pineapple on top of pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Top with coconut.

title: banana chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into egg mixture.
Add bananas and chocolate chips.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
(Caution:
Bananas will darken and become gooey if dough is treated like refrigerator cookies.)

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together and cook till thick.
Pour into a baked pie crust or Graham Crackers.
Can double for 2 pies.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain.
Set aside.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Arrange on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust, sealing perforations completely.
Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken broccoli hot dish
directions: Mix stuffing according to package directions; pat down in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Pour cooked chicken over stuffing.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, butter and peanut butter to a rolling boil, then add oatmeal, cocoa and vanilla.
Beat until like fudge.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pies(makes 3 pies)
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, Pet milk and the rest of the ingredients; mix thoroughly and pour into 3 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease
bottom only of 2 round ring pans. In a large bowl,
blend
first
ingredients.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir
in
remaining ingredients, just until dry ingredients are moistened.	Bake
at
350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: nick's stew (stefatho)
directions: Cube meat 1 1/2 inches, place in deep dish.
Add water to cover and 3 teaspoons of salt.
Soak overnight in refrigerator.

title: bayou seafood casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese and oleo in top of double boiler.
Saute shrimp, onion, pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add cream cheese and oleo.
Blend well.
Add soup, mushrooms, seasonings, crab meat and rice.
Blend well.
Place in oiled 2-quart casserole dish and top with Cheddar and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Freezes well for short time.

title: easy baked shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Leave tail on and butterfly shrimp. Sprinkle Cheese Tid-Bits generously on shrimp. Dot with melted butter.
Add pepper and garlic powder.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli grape salad
directions: Refrigerate first five ingredients.
Before serving time, add mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.

title: evelyn pond's sliced pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin and let stand 20 minutes in a weak salt water.
Drain and add vinegar, sugar and mustard seed and cook 10 minutes after coming to a boil.

title: lamb shish kebab marinade
directions: Heat all together over medium heat and bring to a boil, 8 to 10 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Stir in lamb and marinate 15 minutes or longer. Grill 10 to 15 minutes until done. Pour remaining marinade over lamb before serving.

title: kathy's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Chill until firm.
Add condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Stir until well mixed.
Put layer of wafers in bottom of a large bowl.
Then add a layer of sliced bananas and cover with pudding mixture.
Repeat.

title: chocolate oatmeal crisps
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter on stove.
Add milk, sugar and cocoa. Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in peanut butter, vanilla, salt and oatmeal.
Drop onto waxed paper by spoonfuls. Let cool.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.
Store in airtight container.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Roast, season and slow cook in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours. Or, cook until very tender in a pressure cooker.
Remove the roast from juices and shred.
Save juice for a later use.
Return shredded meat to crock-pot and add the remaining ingredients. Cover and cook 4 to 6 hours.
Discard bay leaf and serve on French rolls or sandwich buns.

title: colorful oven vegetables
directions: Place butter in a shallow 3-quart baking dish. Place in a 400° oven for 5 minutes or until melted. Stir in thyme, salt and pepper. Add the vegetables and toss to coat. Cover and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until the vegetables are crisp and tender.

title: cheese, ham, broccoli strata
directions: Cut 12 inch "doughnuts" and "holes" from bread; set aside. Fit scraps in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, lightly greased.
Place cheese in layers over bread.
Add layer of broccoli, then ham.
Arrange "doughnuts" on top slightly overlapping.
Sprinkle "holes" in center.
May add a few more bread scraps if it looks scarce.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Mix all together and simmer in crock-pot.

title: jean's potato soup(12 servings)
directions: In large pot, saute onion in butter 3 minutes.
Add potatoes, water, celery leaves, salt, pepper, paprika and tomato sauce. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are just tender, stirring occasionally.
In a small skillet, combine oil and flour until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is golden brown.
Watch closely to prevent burning.
Carefully stir into hot soup.
Add parsley.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes or until soup thickens.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and pecans.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Shape in balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: dinner in a pepper
directions: Cut tops off green peppers; discard seeds and membranes.
Chop enough of the tops to make 1/4 cup.
Boil whole peppers for 5 minutes, drain well.
Sprinkle inside lightly with salt.
In skillet, brown beef, onion and the 1/4 cup of green pepper.
Add tomatoes and cook until tender, about 4 minutes.
Drain off liquid.
Add both corns, salt, basil and pepper to skillet.
Mix well.
Stuff peppers with the meat mixture.
Toss crumbs with melted butter, sprinkle on the top of peppers.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: low-fat cheese ball
directions: You can substitute 1 tablespoon of bacon bits if using low-fat dressing.

title: bonbon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: raspberry sauce
directions: Puree ingredients in food processor, then strain.
Cover, chill until ready to use.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Boil eggs.
While macaroni and eggs are cooking, cut up crabmeat.
Have macaroni cool until warm.
In pan mix macaroni, eggs, garlic powder, onion salt, salt and pepper.
Add Miracle Whip until everything is covered and add crabmeat and cucumbers. Pour into bowl.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Serve cold.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels with milk slowly.
Mix flour, oats, sugar, soda, salt and butter.
Press 3/4 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add chocolate chips and peanuts.
Drizzle caramel over top.
Crumble on remaining crumbs and bake 12 minutes more at 350°.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichokes and chop.
Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Add to the artichokes.
Place in ovenproof dish and sprinkle with paprika. Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: cocktail cake
directions: Mix
ingredients
as
given
and
pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts
on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
While warm, frost with Icing.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cut chicken into chunks.
Mix chicken with sour cream, soup and onion soup mix.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare stuffing mix according to directions, using chicken broth for liquid.
Place over the chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and rice in margarine until lightly browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat until rice is tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: amish cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat, then add dry ingredients.
Make dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip glass in sugar and press cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or just until brown (burn easily).
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: marshmallow popcorn
directions: In medium saucepan melt butter and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Pour over popped corn and stir until distributed evenly.
Salt to taste.

title: crab rangoon spread and won ton crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly brush cookie sheet with butter. Cut won tons in half; arrange on sheet.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool on paper towels.
Repeat until won tons are all done.

title: easy french bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Add yeast and water until dough is soft.
Cover and let rise in place (85°) free from drafts for 30 minutes (until doubled).
Turn dough onto heavily floured surface.
Knead to smooth and elastic (5 minutes). Divide in half.
Shape into 2 oval loaves.
Fold over lengthwise and flatten with hands.
Roll each with hands into a 15 x 2-inch loaf.
Twist and place loaves on greased pans.
Brush with butter. Cover and let rise in warm place (85°), free from drafts, until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes, until loaves sound hollow.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan with 4 slices bread.
Mix together all ingredients.
Put half of this mixture on top of the bread in the pan.
Place remaining 4 slices of bread on top and then put the rest of the cheese/egg mixture over them.
Let stand in refrigerator, covered, overnight.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; place half of mixture in bottom of unbaked pastry shell.
Add half of apples and sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Scatter bits of butter.
Repeat until all apples are used.
Squeeze juice of lemon and 1/2 cup water over top.
Top with pastry crust and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oreo pudding
directions: Step 1:
Crumble Oreo cookies (save enough for topping). Place crumbled Oreos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and water over high heat.
Bring to a boil and boil until hard ball forms.
Remove from heat.
Pour in egg whites and beat until thick and workable.
Roll into 1/8-inch thick sheet on a mixture of flour and confectioners sugar.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up into a log, chill and slice.

title: date bread
directions: Mix soda and boiling water; add dates and let set 10 minutes. Mix in with remaining ingredients.
Pour into a loaf pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crusty and firm.

title: peanut butter picnic cake
directions: Grease bottom of a 9-inch x 13-inch baking pan.
Set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, peanut butter, and butter.
Beat until crumbly.
Reserve one cup.
Add baking powder, baking soda, milk, vanilla, and eggs. Blend until smooth.
Pour batter into pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crumbs.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand in pan until cool.
Cut into squares

title: poppy seed bread and cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour into 2 loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Grease pan and sprinkle with sugar.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise and
milk.
Heat
to
boiling
and remove.
Put 1 cup cornflakes in
bottom
of 9 x 13-inch dish. Drain cabbage.
Place on top of cornflakes.
Pour soup mixture over cabbage.
Melt margarine
and	add
with remaining cup of flakes.
Tear cheese into strips.
Put on top of cabbage, then place remaining flakes on top of
cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly.
Bake at 400° about 40 minutes or until nicely browned.
Makes 20 servings.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Wrap breasts with bacon.
Arrange in a baking dish or 9 x 13-inch pan the dried beef on the bottom.
Lay the wrapped chicken breasts over the beef.
Combine the sour cream and mushroom soup. Pour over chicken.
Bake in a 275° oven for 3 hours.
Can be made ahead and reheated.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Cook in hot shortening over medium heat until brown; drain on paper towels.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, salt and water, stirring all the time, until it turns clear.
Take off of heat and add 4 tablespoons strawberry jello.
Let cool.
Put berries in crust and pour filling over it.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: ground beef and rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add soup, water, rice and kix well. Pour into greased casserole dish and bake 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco and add egg.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Make into balls the size of walnut or smaller.
Press down; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar or colored sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Stir in walnuts and orange peel.
Mix in separate bowl, egg, orange juice and oil.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened. Pour into greased loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until tested done (toothpick inserted comes out clean).
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Wrap tightly and store overnight before serving.

title: aunt sara's cheese cake
directions: Mix
jello
and boiling water and place in refrigerator to thicken slightly.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and pour over chicken, beef or pork.
Use with smoked sausage or wieners.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Precook broccoli.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Drain broccoli and pour soup and cheese mixture over broccoli in a 3-quart dish. Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ruby's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together and dissolve the warm water, salt and yeast. Add the cake mix and flour.

title: potato casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine onion, cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, margarine and cheese; mix well.
Thaw hash browns, then add to cream mixture.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch glass baking pan.

title: chicken
directions: Get chicken out of the freezer.
Put it in a pan and cook it in the microwave for 2 minutes.
Get it out, then put on the crumbs and the barbecue sauce.

title: 7-cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: taco dip(makes double recipe; 2 pans)
directions: In 2 small pie pans, spread cream cheese.
Add chili.
Add shredded Monterey Jack, then Cheddar cheese.
Add chopped onions on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve with large corn or tortilla chips, small plates and lots of napkins!

title: spiced devil food cake
directions: Sift flour, spices, soda and salt together. Then cream shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add beaten eggs and chocolate; beat thoroughly. Add sifted dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately. Add boiling water. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: turkey burgers(low calorie)
directions: Preheat broiler.
Spray the broiler with non-stick spray. Lightly combine turkey, onion, egg and parsley and garlic tarragon plus salt and pepper in a bowl.
Form into 4 burgers.
Broil 4-inch from heat until brown, about 5 minutes on each side. 1 Burger = 4 Points.

title: shrimp toasts
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp in saucepan until melted.
Add shrimp.
Spread on English muffins.
Cut each half in six pieces.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Cover or put in bags or plastic container and keep frozen.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes until brown.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a Dutch oven or deep pot, brown roast on all sides to sear in 2 Tbsp. of hot oil.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix, and 1 cup of water.
Reduce heat o low.
Cover and cook for 2 hours, stirring often.
Cook 45 minutes or until roast and vegetables are fork tender.
Remove roast and vegetables.
Stir together flour and remaining 1/4 cup of water until smooth.
Gradually stir in soup mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring often.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening; cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to mixture.
Mix well. Chill very well.
Roll into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.

title: fritos chili pie
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups Fritos in baking dish.
Arrange chopped onions and half of the grated cheese over Fritos.
Pour heated chili over onions and cheese.
Top with remaining Fritos and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Mix all of the above together.
Chill for at least one hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Grate potato and carrots.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Cook in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: new english mulled cider
directions: Put cider in pan.
Add cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add lemon juice.
Slice orange thin; add 1 orange slice to each cup and fill with cider.
Serve hot or cold.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with cheese.
Spread fillets with melted oleo or butter; sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake for 8 to 15 minutes until flaky (depends on thickness of fillets).
Bake at 400°.

title: reception salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice and dissolve Jell-O.
When Jell-O is dissolved, add cream cheese and all other ingredients except whipping cream.
Whip the whipping cream until forms a stiff peak and fold into other mixture.
Pour into mold or 9 x 12-inch dish and refrigerate.

title: hershey's double chocolate mint dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). In a large mixer bowl, beat flour, sugar, butter, eggs and syrup until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
(Top may appear wet.)
Cool completely in pan.
Spread Mint Cream Layer on cake (see recipe).
Chill. Pour Chocolate Topping over dessert (see recipe).
Chill.
Cover.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: unusual pasta
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients for several hours.
Cook pasta according to box directions (use desired amount).
Cook beans or use leftover beans.
Mix everything together and serve.

title: bridge club special
directions: Mix flour, chopped nuts and oleo together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip; spread over cooled crust.
Cook puddings using 1/2 milk in each pudding; let cool.
Layer over cream cheese mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: pudding pops
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Pour into six 5 ounce paper cups, or pop molds.
Insert wooden stick or plastic spoons.
Place a small piece of plastic wrap over top.
Freeze until firm.
Press firm on bottom of cups to release pop and serve.

title: antipasta salad
directions: Mix all together.
Cover with garlic salt and enough oil to coat.
Let set overnight for flavors to mix.

title: vegetable beef soup made with ground beef
directions: Brown and drain hamburg.
Cover with water.
Add bouillon cubes and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add pepper and more seasoning to taste.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Combine the blackberries, sugar and tapioca in a large bowl and let set, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Spoon into unbaked pie shell.
Cut the butter or margarine on top.
Cover with crust. Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Reduce heat to 375° and bake for 45 minutes more.

title: coffee cake
directions: Add flour, apple pie filling and raisins or nuts to cake mix. Make it in 2 loaf pans, greased slightly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Line a 14-inch pizza pan with slices overlapping slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool. Blend softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cookie crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese layer.
Glaze with marmalade or preserves which have been mixed with water.

title: webb stew
directions: Boil hamburg until done.
Place onion and potatoes in same pot and cook until done.
Add tomato soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve when hot.

title: hermits
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar until smooth.
Add eggs; blend well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon salt, allspice and cloves.
Gradually blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from baking sheet to a wire rack to cool.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Heat
tomato
soup;
thoroughly blend cream cheese into soup (may
need to use whisk).
Soften gelatin in cold water. Dissolve gelatin mixture in hot soup and cream cheese;
cool. Add
all other ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart fish-shaped mold
and chill until firm.
Unmold and serve with crackers or party rye.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread out in a greased shallow pan. Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with zucchini to egg mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Freezes well.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: steak and dressing
directions: Stuff steak with dressing and tie with a clean string.
Bake at 275°
for 4 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain.
In meantime, in medium bowl combine egg, Parmesan cheese and butter.
Add spaghetti; toss well.
Put mixture in bottom of 9 x 3-inch pan.

title: fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar in large saucepan over low heat.
Bring to boiling; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove pan from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Stir with wooden spoon until marshmallows are melted.
Pour fudge into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut into squares when completely cool.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given except the butter and vanilla.
Cook over boiling water until mixture thickens, stirring often.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.

title: baked flank steak
directions: Set oven at 450°.
Use flat baking dish large enough for steak. Set dish in oven for 5 minutes.
Blend butter and seasoning and add to dish.
When butter melts, add steak.
Bake 5 minutes and turn steak.
Bake another 5 minutes (or more).
Slice steak on diagonal and turn each slice in seasonings in dish.
Serve in dish.

title: grilled ribs
directions: Combine onion and oil in a 4-cup glass measure.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in chili sauce and next 5 ingredients.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, until slightly thickened, stirring after 2 minutes.
Set aside.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions.
Drain, reserving cooking liquid.
Cook onion in reserved cooking liquid for 5 minutes or until tender.
Do not drain.
In screw-top jar, combine milk, cornstarch, salt, thyme and dash of pepper.
Shake, mixing well.
Stir into onion.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in Neufchatel cheese.
Add broccoli.
Gently stir to mix.
Turn into serving bowl.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Combine and serve in lettuce cups with thin slices of chicken on top.
Garnish with stuffed olives (diced thin) or chopped ripe olives.
Let chill in refrigerator.
Makes great sandwiches.

title: eight layer salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl in the order listed.
Do not toss!

title: ham buns
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and spoon into hot dog buns. Wrap in aluminum foil and bake for 10 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Or cover buns with wax paper and heat in the microwave until heated with the cheese melted.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon, onions and beef. Drain off fat. Stir in seasonings. Add all the beans. Stir and cook 1/2 hour.
Serve with crusty buns and salad.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise with curry, lemon juice, garlic salt and soy sauce.
Mix first 4 ingredients with mayonnaise mixture.
Just before serving add pecans and noodles.

title: lemon cheze filling or frosting
directions: Mix.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Spread onto two-layer cakes.

title: easy nacho dip
directions: Layer in 10-inch glass baking dish cream cheese, Hormel chili, then Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Dip nacho chips.

title: butterscotch haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in top of double boiler or you may use microwave.
Add peanut butter.
Stir.
Pour over noodles.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop onto waxed paper by spoonful.
Should look like small stacks.

title: rice meat balls
directions: Combine rice with beef, egg, onion, salt, marjoram, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato juice. Mix lightly. Shape mixture into 18 balls and place in skillet. Add sugar to remaining 2 cups of tomato juice. Pour juice over meat balls in skillet. Bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 15 minutes, basting occasionally. Makes 6 servings of 3 meat balls each.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Then add all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer one hour.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips and 14 oz. almond bark (I use microwave at 60% power).
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased or foil-covered 12 inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries; sprinkle with coconut.
Melt remaining 2 oz. almond bark and drizzle over coconut.
Chill until firm. Store at room temperature.

title: karen lewis's peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches and juice in long cake pan.
Sprinkle Jell-O over peaches.
Sprinkle cake mix over Jell-O.
Cut up butter over top of this.
Pour water over this.
Sprinkle nuts over top if desired. Do not stir or mix.
Bake at 350° until done (about 30 to 45 minutes).
Will be brown on top.
Very rich!

title: w. w. potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in chicken broth until tender. Mix gravy mix in 1/2 cup cold water. Add to potatoes and stir until thick.
tags: Pioneer no fat country gravy mix

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cook cut up tomatoes, onions, green peppers and basil until vegetables are done.
Put through a colander.
Add salad oil, oregano, sugar, salt and tomato paste.
Cook until thick like sauce.
Put in jars, seal and process for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate whacky cake
directions: Sift
together all dry ingredients
into ungreased cake pan. Make
3 holes in dry ingredients.
In one hole fill with oil; in another
put
vinegar; and in the last hole, vanilla. Pour cold water
over all and stir with fork until mixed very well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: holiday carrot cake
directions: Blend all dry ingredients.
Mix in oil, eggs and carrots. Blend well.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 50 minutes (or until toothpick comes out clean).

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in covered 1 1/2-quart dish.

title: cocoa-licious cereal treats
directions: Melt margarine in a 5-quart saucepan on low until melted.
Add marshmallows and melt until smooth.
Remove from heat and add cereal, coating well.
Press firmly into lightly greased foil lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Turn onto cutting surface.
Peel off foil and cut into squares.

title: fried salmon patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form into 10 to 12 patties and fry until medium brown in lightly oiled skillet. Drain on paper towels.
Serves 4.

title: city chicken barbecue
directions: You will need 12 to 15 wooden skewers, 4 1/2 to 5-inches long.

title: *diet cake*
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups of water until dry.
Mix all ingredients together; blend well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for
1 hour.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Mix together first 10 ingredients.
This is your marinade. Wipe meat with damp paper towels.
Put meat in marinade.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 days, turning meat occasionally.
Remove meat from marinade.
Reserve marinade.
Dry off meat with paper towels. Coat meat with 2 tablespoons flour.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Puree 1/2 cup strawberries and honey in blender or food processor.
Add milk and yogurt; blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses; garnish each with whole strawberry.
Yield: About 2 cups.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix
oatmeal
and boiling water.
Let stand 20 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: baked western omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray a 10-inch glass pie pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl with wire whisk, beat eggs with 1/4 cup of water until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients with rubber spatula.
Scrape into prepared pie pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes until omelet is set, slightly puffed and browned.
Cut into 4 servings and serve at once.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container.
Store in covered container.
Use 1/4 to 1/3 cup of mix for each cup of hot cocoa. Use hot water mixed with cocoa mix to make hot cocoa.

title: banana pudding
directions: Reserve 1 banana and 10 to 12 vanilla wafers for garnish. Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk.
Blend well; cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Spread small amount on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with layer of sliced banana.
Pour about 1/3 of custard over banana.
Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard to make 3 layers of each, ending with custard.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Spoon on top of pudding, spreading to cover entire surface, sealing well to edges.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until delicately brown.
Cool slightly or chill.
Just before serving, garnish with banana slices, then wafers, upright around edges of dish.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute ground beef, pepperoni, onion and green pepper lightly. Melt butter and place in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Toss cooked spaghetti with butter.
Cover with one can tomato sauce.
Add half the cheese and half the meat mixture and all the mushrooms. Sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Add remaining cheese and meat. Top with 2nd can of tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: butter pecan torte
directions: Beat together until smooth.
Pour in cool crust.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Beat 1/2 pint of whipping cream and pour over the mixture.
Sprinkle with 4 Heath bars (crushed).

title: classic meat loaf(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: I also add chopped bell pepper and 1 tablespoon cooking oil.

title: spaghetti soup
directions: Break spaghetti into bite size pieces and cook.
Drain.
Bring tomato juice just to boil.
Add pasta and black pepper to taste. Serve.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt margarine; add graham crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: molasses crunches
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill well.
Roll into 1-inch balls, then roll in sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet at 375°.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients into a large bowl and mix well. Store mix in airtight container.

title: rice-cooker seafood jambalaya
directions: All seasoning should be chopped fine; mix all into rice cooker, cover and
turn
on.
Cooks in 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir completely and
leave
cooker
on warm for few minutes.
(Cook beef, chicken, pork, sausage or crabmeat may be substituted.)

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Christmas Eve night, cook sausage; drain. Beat eggs and milk well. Add bread, cheese and sausage. Put in greased casserole and cover with foil. Place in the refrigerator. Christmas morning, place casserole in cold oven at 350°. Cook, uncovered, 45 minutes.

title: cheesy artichoke squares
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch glass pan with 1 teaspoon butter or margarine.
Saute onion, garlic and parsley in a little butter until onion is translucent.
Meanwhile, drain and chop artichoke hearts.
While they are still "draining," beat eggs until they are light.
Add bread crumbs and seasonings.
Mix well.
Stir in cheese, sauteed onion, garlic and parsley and artichoke hearts. Put in greased pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°, until it feels firm to touch.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: s'mores
directions: Preheat broiler.
Arrange half of graham crackers on baking sheet.
Top each cracker with 1 piece of the chocolate bars.
Broil until chocolate is softened, but not melted.
Arrange 2 tablespoons marshmallows on each cracker.
Broil until lightly toasted.
Top with remaining crackers and serve.
Makes 8 S'mores.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ez potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tempting pretzel snack
directions: Break pretzels into pieces.
Lay on cookie sheet.
In a bowl, mix other ingredients.
Pour over pretzels.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, turning every 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts and set aside. Combine remaining ingredients. Add to dry; stir until moistened. Spoon batter into prepared pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until not moist in middle when tested. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans and place on wire racks; cool completely.

title: individual strawberry shortcakes
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure.
Add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk all at once and stir carefully until all flour is dampened.
Then stir vigorously until mixture forms a soft dough and follows spoon around bowl.
Drop 3/4 cup dough onto ungreased baking sheet*.
Brush with milk (or cream). Bake in hot oven (450°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake about 1 hour at 300°.

title: dandelion wine
directions: Bring water to a boil, add sugar and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Put in blossoms, let stand until lukewarm.
Add yeast, dissolved in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Let stand 7 days, stirring in the morning and night.
After 7 days, strain through cheesecloth. Add raisins and lemon juice, let stand 2 weeks.
Do not stir! Strain after 2 weeks and put in bottles.
Do not cap too tightly. Let stand for 3 weeks before drinking.

title: barbecue roast
directions: Slash edge of meat, sprinkle both sides with meat tenderizer and let stand 1 hour.

title: fantastic fruit salad
directions: Blend Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip, then add pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix onion dip and cream cheese, place in a 9x13 pan.
